Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.20,0:00:10.24,English,,0,0,0,,Richard Feynman was one of the most extraordinary scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.24,0:00:12.16,English,,0,0,0,,of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.16,0:00:14.16,English,,0,0,0,,As a brilliant physicist,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,he pioneered an entirely new area of his subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.64,0:00:20.88,English,,0,0,0,,He's discovered a new law of nature, only a very few people did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.88,0:00:25.16,English,,0,0,0,,The most numerically precise physical theory ever invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.16,0:00:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,Yet, he scorned the Nobel Prize he received for this work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.60,0:00:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,I've already got the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.44,0:00:33.88,English,,0,0,0,,The prize is the pleasure of finding the thing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.88,0:00:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,The kick in the discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.32,0:00:38.36,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's brilliance helped shape history.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:41.56,English,,0,0,0,,As a young man, he helped to build the atom bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:43.76,English,,0,0,0,,ending the Second World War.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:47.08,English,,0,0,0,,And yet, throughout his life, Feynman rejected authority
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.08,0:00:48.92,English,,0,0,0,,and refused to conform,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.92,0:00:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,preferring instead to follow his passions -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.96,0:00:54.00,English,,0,0,0,,from bongo playing to biology,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.00,0:00:56.00,English,,0,0,0,,from poetry to painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:58.40,English,,0,0,0,,from computing to cracking safes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.40,0:01:01.36,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's fascination with the world knew no bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.12,0:01:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,And in his dying days,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.64,0:01:08.36,English,,0,0,0,,as a maverick investigator on the Challenger shuttle disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.36,0:01:10.96,English,,0,0,0,,he confronted the Washington establishment
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.96,0:01:13.92,English,,0,0,0,,to reveal the truth about what went wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.92,0:01:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,This stuff that I got out of your seal,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.96,0:01:18.80,English,,0,0,0,,and I put it in ice water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:22.52,English,,0,0,0,,Above all, Feynman's infectious enthusiasm for life
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.52,0:01:25.28,English,,0,0,0,,captivated millions of readers and viewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.28,0:01:28.68,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's been a showman pretty much his whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.68,0:01:31.92,English,,0,0,0,,Any room he walked into, everyone is looking at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.92,0:01:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,He was the centre of attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.80,0:01:38.48,English,,0,0,0,,Electrons behave exactly the same in this respect as protons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.48,0:01:43.40,English,,0,0,0,,That is, they're both screwy, but in exactly the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.40,0:01:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,Here, in his own words and those of the people who knew him best,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.04,0:01:51.88,English,,0,0,0,,this is the story of the most captivating communicator
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:54.12,English,,0,0,0,,in the history of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:57.28,English,,0,0,0,,But you got to stop and think about the complexity,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:01.00,English,,0,0,0,,the INCONCEIVABLE nature of nature!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.56,0:02:24.28,English,,0,0,0,,When my mother was pregnant first,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.28,0:02:27.40,English,,0,0,0,,my father said, "If he's a boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,"I want him to be a scientist."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,Richard Phillips Feynman was born on the 11th May 1918,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.04,0:02:38.00,English,,0,0,0,,during the Depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:41.48,English,,0,0,0,,to working-class parents living in the outskirts of New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.68,0:02:46.12,English,,0,0,0,,Even when I was a small boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.12,0:02:48.36,English,,0,0,0,,Poppa used to sit me on his lap
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.36,0:02:51.24,English,,0,0,0,,and read to me from the Encyclopaedia Britannica.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:55.68,English,,0,0,0,,And he would read, say, about dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.68,0:02:57.48,English,,0,0,0,,It would say something like,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:00.96,English,,0,0,0,,"This thing is 25 feet high
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.96,0:03:03.80,English,,0,0,0,,"and the head is six feet across."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:08.12,English,,0,0,0,,And so, he'd stop always and say, "Let's see what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:11.20,English,,0,0,0,,"That would mean that if he stood in our front yard,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.20,0:03:14.56,English,,0,0,0,,"he would be high enough to put his head through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.56,0:03:17.76,English,,0,0,0,,"But not quite, cos the head is a little bit too wide."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,It was very exciting and interesting to think
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.08,0:03:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,that there were animals of such magnitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.08,0:03:25.00,English,,0,0,0,,and that they all died out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.00,0:03:27.48,English,,0,0,0,,and at that time, nobody knew why.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.76,0:03:31.44,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the way I was educated by my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.52,0:03:37.24,English,,0,0,0,,By the age of ten, Richard had his own science laboratory at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.32,English,,0,0,0,,where he tinkered with old radios
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:41.76,English,,0,0,0,,and experimented with physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:46.64,English,,0,0,0,,He hired me, for four cents a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.36,English,,0,0,0,,as his lab assistant,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:51.92,English,,0,0,0,,to amaze his friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.92,0:03:54.16,English,,0,0,0,,You know, there was a spark gap
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.16,0:03:55.96,English,,0,0,0,,with voltage against it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:03:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,..and if you put your finger in,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.48,0:04:01.64,English,,0,0,0,,you get a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,It was my job, as part of my four cents,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.52,0:04:09.28,English,,0,0,0,,to put my finger in this spark gap for his friends' amusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.36,0:04:14.88,English,,0,0,0,,Their father, Melville Feynman,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.88,0:04:17.84,English,,0,0,0,,worked for a company which made uniforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.84,0:04:22.12,English,,0,0,0,,This exposure to the military led to a strong rejection of authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.12,0:04:24.44,English,,0,0,0,,a value he instilled in his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:29.28,English,,0,0,0,,One of the things that my father taught me was a disrespect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:34.12,English,,0,0,0,,He'd open a picture, a New York Times, maybe it was a General,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.12,0:04:36.72,English,,0,0,0,,and he'd say, "Now, look at these humans," he'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:39.68,English,,0,0,0,,"Here's one human standing here and all these others are bowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.68,0:04:42.36,English,,0,0,0,,"Now, what is the difference? Why are they all bowing to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:44.52,English,,0,0,0,,"Only because of his name and his position.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.52,0:04:45.80,English,,0,0,0,,"Because of his uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:48.36,English,,0,0,0,,"Not because of something he especially did."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.72,0:04:56.12,English,,0,0,0,,At the age of 17, Feynman won a maths competition in New York
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.12,0:04:58.20,English,,0,0,0,,and it became clear this was a subject
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.20,0:05:00.84,English,,0,0,0,,in which he was greatly gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.84,0:05:04.24,English,,0,0,0,,In 1935, he was awarded a place
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.24,0:05:08.72,English,,0,0,0,,at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, MIT.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:11.24,English,,0,0,0,,But away from home for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.24,0:05:14.00,English,,0,0,0,,he was going to miss more than just his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.64,0:05:18.52,English,,0,0,0,,She was very beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:20.36,English,,0,0,0,,Arline Greenbaum,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,the most beautiful girl on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.36,0:05:29.64,English,,0,0,0,,She had great dimples and long hair down to here, when she unbraided it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.04,0:05:32.48,English,,0,0,0,,Oh, we loved her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:35.72,English,,0,0,0,,They were not officially engaged, she was only 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:37.56,English,,0,0,0,,She was sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:40.40,English,,0,0,0,,We all loved her, she loved all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.88,0:05:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,From MIT, Feynman movedto Princeton,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:50.96,English,,0,0,0,,achieving full marks in the maths and physics entrance exam -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:52.96,English,,0,0,0,,an unprecedented feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:05:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,But back home, things weren't as perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.72,0:06:05.76,English,,0,0,0,,The family went away for a spring vacation
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.76,0:06:08.20,English,,0,0,0,,with Arline.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.20,0:06:10.32,English,,0,0,0,,We went swimming
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:14.52,English,,0,0,0,,and my father saw this lump on Arline's neck
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:17.08,English,,0,0,0,,and said to her, "What is that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,And she didn't know, but she went to a doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:23.24,English,,0,0,0,,and it was the tuberculosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:27.16,English,,0,0,0,,We were all heartbroken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.16,0:06:30.88,English,,0,0,0,,It was before there was any medicine for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.88,0:06:34.92,English,,0,0,0,,And although she was sick and dying, he married her,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.92,0:06:38.28,English,,0,0,0,,because he wanted to take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:40.32,English,,0,0,0,,It was very hard on my mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.32,0:06:43.56,English,,0,0,0,,because she was afraid he would catch tuberculosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:46.20,English,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.24,0:06:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,..my mother wasn't given a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.60,0:06:56.76,English,,0,0,0,,The couple braced themselves for life in the shadow of TB.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.76,0:07:00.64,English,,0,0,0,,But another menace was about to disrupt their time together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.04,0:07:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,Just months before Richard and Arline were married,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.08,0:07:19.40,English,,0,0,0,,America was drawn into the Second World War,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:21.60,English,,0,0,0,,following the bombing of Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman was asked if he wanted to join a top-secret project
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:31.28,English,,0,0,0,,based in a Government laboratory at Los Alamos, in New Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.92,0:07:35.08,English,,0,0,0,,Code-named Manhattan,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.08,0:07:37.52,English,,0,0,0,,its objective was to build an atom bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.20,0:07:40.84,English,,0,0,0,,The fear was that Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:43.68,English,,0,0,0,,would invent such a terrifying new weapon first
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.68,0:07:45.24,English,,0,0,0,,and use it to win the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:51.48,English,,0,0,0,,There was nothing that I knew that indicated
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.48,0:07:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,that if we could do it, they couldn't do it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.88,0:07:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,and therefore, it was very important to try to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.68,0:07:59.28,English,,0,0,0,,Germany was the centre,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:03.00,English,,0,0,0,,the intellectual centre of theoretical physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:07.48,English,,0,0,0,,They knew the power of this - that if Germany got this first,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.48,0:08:10.48,English,,0,0,0,,we have to make sure that they don't rule the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.64,0:08:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,I felt I should do in order to protect civilisation, if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.52,0:08:22.52,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman became a member of the Manhattan Project at Los Alamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.52,0:08:25.96,English,,0,0,0,,Here, he joined some of the world's finest physicists,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:29.40,English,,0,0,0,,pooling their combined brainpower to try to create the bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.24,0:08:38.92,English,,0,0,0,,Oppenheimer was in charge of the scientific or engineering side.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.92,0:08:41.32,English,,0,0,0,,And he was quite a heavyweight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.32,0:08:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,Fermi, Niels Bohr...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.24,0:08:48.12,English,,0,0,0,,You know, the big names of extremely high level.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:08:51.76,English,,0,0,0,,Despite being surrounded by extraordinary physicists,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:55.40,English,,0,0,0,,the challenge of developing an atom bomb so quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.40,0:08:57.60,English,,0,0,0,,was an enormous undertaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.60,0:08:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,One fundamental problem
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.48,0:09:03.24,English,,0,0,0,,was the sheer volume of calculations required.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:06.12,English,,0,0,0,,Without computers, it had to be done manually,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.12,0:09:08.16,English,,0,0,0,,slowing progress enormously.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.16,0:09:11.08,English,,0,0,0,,That was, until Feynman arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.08,0:09:16.16,English,,0,0,0,,He found a way to get calculations going in parallel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:22.00,English,,0,0,0,,Still manually, still each person doing one operation at a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.00,0:09:24.92,English,,0,0,0,,but working in parallel and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.92,0:09:29.48,English,,0,0,0,,having the parts of the calculation come back together later,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,so that three problems in nine months got turned around
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.20,0:09:36.56,English,,0,0,0,,to nine big problems done in three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.56,0:09:41.08,English,,0,0,0,,'I put on the blackboard a challenge, "Can we do it?", to the boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:44.84,English,,0,0,0,,'They all start, "Yes, we'll work double shifts, we'll work overtime,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,'"We'll try it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.52,0:09:49.84,English,,0,0,0,,'As a result, we did problems nearly ten times as fast.'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.48,0:09:54.72,English,,0,0,0,,He somehow got this team of human computers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.72,0:09:57.36,English,,0,0,0,,to work at an inhuman pace
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:59.08,English,,0,0,0,,and got things to roll.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:01.88,English,,0,0,0,,And that was when his scientific seniors,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.88,0:10:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,the big shots of science at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:07.72,English,,0,0,0,,first became aware of this fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.72,0:10:09.36,English,,0,0,0,,Despite being a key member
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:12.40,English,,0,0,0,,of the most secret Government project of the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.40,0:10:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's streak of maverick mischief was never far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.04,0:10:20.48,English,,0,0,0,,'So I used to pick the locks all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:22.76,English,,0,0,0,,'and point out that it was very easy to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:26.00,English,,0,0,0,,'and every time we had a meeting of the whole...everybody together,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:28.64,English,,0,0,0,,'I'd get up and I'd say that we have important secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:32.28,English,,0,0,0,,'and we shouldn't keep them in such thing. We need better locks!'
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.60,0:10:36.80,English,,0,0,0,,Between safecracking and doing physics calculations,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:40.12,English,,0,0,0,,the pace of life at Los Alamos was relentless.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.12,0:10:43.04,English,,0,0,0,,But for Feynman, it was a welcome distraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.04,0:10:47.44,English,,0,0,0,,In a sanatorium nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.44,0:10:50.96,English,,0,0,0,,his wife Arline was confined to her bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:53.00,English,,0,0,0,,slowly dying of her disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:57.08,English,,0,0,0,,At that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.08,0:11:00.84,English,,0,0,0,,dry climates were believed to be good for tuberculosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:04.20,English,,0,0,0,,So although he was at high altitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.20,0:11:07.24,English,,0,0,0,,she was at a lower altitude, in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,I remember the day she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.16,0:11:15.12,English,,0,0,0,,She was 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:19.60,English,,0,0,0,,He was 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.04,0:11:22.76,English,,0,0,0,,He was broken-hearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:31.84,English,,0,0,0,,Then, in the aftermath of his grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:34.64,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman was forced to confront the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:36.88,English,,0,0,0,,of what he had helped create.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:43.56,English,,0,0,0,,'They gave out dark glasses that you could watch it with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.56,0:11:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,'20 miles away,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.00,0:11:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,'you are not going to see a damn thing through dark glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.84,0:11:50.92,English,,0,0,0,,'Well, I figured the only thing that could really hurt your eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.92,0:11:54.20,English,,0,0,0,,'bright light never can hurt your eyes, is ultraviolet light that does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.20,0:11:56.64,English,,0,0,0,,'So I got behind a truck windshield,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:00.04,English,,0,0,0,,'so the ultraviolet can't go through glass, so that would be safe
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:02.04,English,,0,0,0,,'and so, I could see the damn thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.96,0:12:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,'I'm about the only guy in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:14.44,English,,0,0,0,,'that actually looked at the damn thing in the first Trinity test.'
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.56,0:12:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,Three weeks later, America prepared to detonate a second atom bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:40.80,English,,0,0,0,,This time, it wasn't a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.08,0:12:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,He had been...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.72,0:12:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,..expected to go as the scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.20,English,,0,0,0,,with the first flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.36,0:12:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,But the bomb was so successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.68,0:13:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,they decided they didn't need a scientist, so he did not go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:05.24,English,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he would have been in that plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.92,0:13:15.48,English,,0,0,0,,The bomb exploded above the Japanese city of Hiroshima,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:18.48,English,,0,0,0,,on the 6th August 1945.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:20.96,English,,0,0,0,,It killed more than 80,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:26.16,English,,0,0,0,,Three days later, a second bomb was detonated - at Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.64,0:13:31.84,English,,0,0,0,,There was a very considerable elation and excitement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.84,0:13:36.52,English,,0,0,0,,And there was kind of parties and people got drunk and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:45.16,English,,0,0,0,,..it would make a tremendously interesting contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,of what was going on in Los Alamos
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.52,0:13:51.16,English,,0,0,0,,at the same time as what was going on in Hiroshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:53.96,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman was deeply disturbed by the knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:56.52,English,,0,0,0,,he had contributed to the deaths of so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.56,0:14:03.44,English,,0,0,0,,He had had this great triumph on the technical level at Los Alamos,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:07.44,English,,0,0,0,,and then, of course, a terrible let down afterwards...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:12.96,English,,0,0,0,,..having run this tremendous race, and then, at the end of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.96,0:14:14.96,English,,0,0,0,,concluding that it wasn't, in fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.76,0:14:18.48,English,,0,0,0,,..worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.48,0:14:21.32,English,,0,0,0,,In the months after this double trauma -
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.32,0:14:23.24,English,,0,0,0,,first, losing his wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.24,0:14:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,then, realising the destruction he'd helped unleash,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:29.16,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman was thrown into darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.28,0:14:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe from just the bomb itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:35.84,English,,0,0,0,,and maybe for some other psychological reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.84,0:14:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,I had just lost my wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.40,0:14:41.00,English,,0,0,0,,I was really in a kind of depressive condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:14:58.96,English,,0,0,0,,In the autumn of 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:01.64,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman was invited to become a professor
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.64,0:15:04.96,English,,0,0,0,,in the Physics Department at Cornell University.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:08.20,English,,0,0,0,,But he was still shaken by the events of the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.20,0:15:11.12,English,,0,0,0,,They expected me to be wonderful to offer me a job like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:12.64,English,,0,0,0,,and I wasn't wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:15.88,English,,0,0,0,,I though to myself, "I haven't done anything important.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.88,0:15:18.84,English,,0,0,0,,"And I'm never going to do anything important."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:22.48,English,,0,0,0,,But I used to enjoy physics and mathematical things
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.48,0:15:25.68,English,,0,0,0,,and because I used to play with it, it was never very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.68,0:15:28.04,English,,0,0,0,,But I used to do things for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.04,0:15:30.88,English,,0,0,0,,So I decided, I'm going to do things only for the fun of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:35.64,English,,0,0,0,,While Feynman was rediscovering the fun in physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.64,0:15:38.32,English,,0,0,0,,science was in crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:42.24,English,,0,0,0,,For many years, new discoveries about how atoms behave
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:44.96,English,,0,0,0,,had been throwing physics into turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:48.88,English,,0,0,0,,Old assumptions about the world were being proved wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.60,0:15:55.24,English,,0,0,0,,This new problematic area of physics was christened Quantum Mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.36,0:15:59.32,English,,0,0,0,,Quantum Mechanics, in a lot of ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,was the most profound psychological shock
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.76,0:16:04.68,English,,0,0,0,,that physicists have ever had in all of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.68,0:16:06.40,English,,0,0,0,,Newton was not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.40,0:16:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,You can know everything there is to know about the world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.52,English,,0,0,0,,and yet, you cannot predict with perfect accuracy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:14.76,English,,0,0,0,,what will happen next.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.76,0:16:17.60,English,,0,0,0,,Quantum Mechanics had revealed the problems
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:20.36,English,,0,0,0,,of accurately predicting how atoms
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.36,0:16:23.08,English,,0,0,0,,and their electromagnetic forces would behave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.56,0:16:27.84,English,,0,0,0,,And because these are the fundamental building blocks
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.84,0:16:31.00,English,,0,0,0,,of nature, it threw everything else into doubt too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.64,0:16:35.88,English,,0,0,0,,Everything that happens around you, other than gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.88,0:16:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,all the immediately experienceable parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,are electromagnetism at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.60,0:16:45.48,English,,0,0,0,,When two atoms get together to form a molecule,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:49.60,English,,0,0,0,,that's electromagnetism, so all of chemistry is electromagnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.60,0:16:52.36,English,,0,0,0,,And if that means all of chemistry is electromagnetism,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:54.16,English,,0,0,0,,then, guess what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,All of biology is electromagnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:01.68,English,,0,0,0,,Literally, everything around us is a manifestation of electromagnetism
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.68,0:17:03.28,English,,0,0,0,,one way or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,A new field, called Quantum Electro-Dynamics, or QED, emerged
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.72,0:17:12.44,English,,0,0,0,,to try to make sense of electromagnetism
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.44,0:17:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,and sub-atomic matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.48,0:17:17.76,English,,0,0,0,,Sometimes QED seemed to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:20.36,English,,0,0,0,,but other times, its predictions were way off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:25.48,English,,0,0,0,,It was all crazy, it didn't make any sense. It gave you infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.48,0:17:27.84,English,,0,0,0,,Infinity is not an answer. Nothing is infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.84,0:17:30.68,English,,0,0,0,,We don't measure in the lab infinity, you get a finite answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,You can't have your basic fundamental theory of physics
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:35.40,English,,0,0,0,,give you infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.40,0:17:37.40,English,,0,0,0,,These predictions of infinity
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:40.96,English,,0,0,0,,were stumping the smartest physicists on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:45.20,English,,0,0,0,,Even the father of QED, Paul Dirac, was foxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:48.00,English,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, I read Dirac's book,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:51.00,English,,0,0,0,,and he had these problems that nobody knew how to solve
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:52.28,English,,0,0,0,,which he described there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.28,0:17:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,I couldn't understand the book very well
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:56.12,English,,0,0,0,,because I really wasn't up to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:17:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,But there, in the last paragraph at the end of the book, it said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:02.40,English,,0,0,0,,"Some new ideas are here needed."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:05.16,English,,0,0,0,,And so, there I was, some new ideas were needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:08.04,English,,0,0,0,,OK, so I started to think of new ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:09.92,English,,0,0,0,,Perhaps typically,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.92,0:18:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's inspiration for his new ideas was unconventional.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.00,0:18:17.48,English,,0,0,0,,When I was eating lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:20.48,English,,0,0,0,,some kid threw up a plate in the cafeteria
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.48,0:18:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,which has a blue medallion on the plate,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:26.68,English,,0,0,0,,the Cornell sign in the cafeteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.68,0:18:29.40,English,,0,0,0,,And as he threw up the plate and it came down,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.40,0:18:33.64,English,,0,0,0,,it wobbled and the blue thing went around like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.64,0:18:36.28,English,,0,0,0,,And I wondered what the relation was between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.28,0:18:37.52,English,,0,0,0,,See, I was just playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.52,0:18:39.44,English,,0,0,0,,No importance at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.44,0:18:41.60,English,,0,0,0,,So I played around with the equations
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.60,0:18:44.48,English,,0,0,0,,of motion of rotating things.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:47.28,English,,0,0,0,,And I kept continuing to play with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.28,0:18:50.16,English,,0,0,0,,And this rotation lead me to a similar problem
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.16,0:18:52.36,English,,0,0,0,,of the rotational of the spin of the electron
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:54.20,English,,0,0,0,,according to Dirac's equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.20,0:18:55.80,English,,0,0,0,,And that just lead me back
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.80,0:18:57.64,English,,0,0,0,,into quantum electro-dynamics
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.64,0:18:59.00,English,,0,0,0,,Everything just poured out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:00.52,English,,0,0,0,,It was just like letting a cork
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.52,0:19:01.88,English,,0,0,0,,out of a bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.40,0:19:07.36,English,,0,0,0,,Inspired by the spinning plate,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.36,0:19:11.24,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman realised that the fact the equations resulted in infinity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.24,0:19:13.72,English,,0,0,0,,didn't mean they were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.72,0:19:17.40,English,,0,0,0,,The problem just needed to be looked at from a new perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:20.48,English,,0,0,0,,It turns out that that kind of challenge was perfectly suited
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.48,0:19:22.52,English,,0,0,0,,for someone like Richard Feynman,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.52,0:19:26.68,English,,0,0,0,,who, surprisingly maybe, didn't like to speculate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,He wasn't the kind of modern physicist that we celebrate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:32.52,English,,0,0,0,,who's always coming up with a new theory of the multi-verse
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:34.24,English,,0,0,0,,or forces of nature or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.24,0:19:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,He really liked to work in the context
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.12,0:19:39.32,English,,0,0,0,,of things that were supposed to be understood
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.32,0:19:42.16,English,,0,0,0,,and just understand them better than anybody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,To work around the infinites in QED,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.04,0:19:50.28,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman came up with a truly revolutionary idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:54.92,English,,0,0,0,,It was such a strange solution not even his sister,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.92,0:19:57.16,English,,0,0,0,,by then, a physicist herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.16,0:19:59.20,English,,0,0,0,,recognised it as serious work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:04.16,English,,0,0,0,,Richard said to me, "Would you go in the room and get my papers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.16,0:20:07.12,English,,0,0,0,,"I want to start working and my papers are in there."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.12,0:20:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,So I went in the room, and I looked...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,there was no mathematics, it was these silly little diagrams,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,and I came out and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:17.96,English,,0,0,0,,"Richard, I can't find your papers,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.96,0:20:19.72,English,,0,0,0,,"it's just these kind
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.72,0:20:21.48,English,,0,0,0,,"of silly diagrams."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:24.60,English,,0,0,0,,He says, "That is my work!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.68,0:20:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,The simple little diagrams Feynman had invented
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.12,0:20:36.16,English,,0,0,0,,were a brilliant way to sidestep the complicated calculations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.16,0:20:38.00,English,,0,0,0,,required for QED.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,They were a sort of shortcut,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.84,0:20:41.84,English,,0,0,0,,allowing him to avoid the infinities
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:45.28,English,,0,0,0,,and make meaningful predictions about the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.28,0:20:48.96,English,,0,0,0,,He saw that there was actually a sort of pictorial way
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.96,0:20:52.36,English,,0,0,0,,of thinking about these pictures, these equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.36,0:20:54.60,English,,0,0,0,,You could associate a little cartoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.60,0:20:57.72,English,,0,0,0,,a little Feynman diagram, as we now call them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.72,0:21:00.16,English,,0,0,0,,to every one of these terms in the equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,Other people would have to work for months
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.52,0:21:05.20,English,,0,0,0,,and he would get it in an afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:07.72,English,,0,0,0,,And eventually, that's what got his ideas noticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.72,0:21:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,because he's getting the right answer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.68,0:21:11.56,English,,0,0,0,,and he's doing it much simpler,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:15.00,English,,0,0,0,,even though no-one understood what he was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:18.08,English,,0,0,0,,It turns out to be so useful that now we're applying it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:21.44,English,,0,0,0,,to completely different fields that aren't particle physics at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,When we look at the evolution of galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.64,0:21:25.72,English,,0,0,0,,and large scale structure in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:27.56,English,,0,0,0,,we're finding that Feynman diagrams
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.56,0:21:31.24,English,,0,0,0,,are a helpful way of calculating those quantities as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:36.80,English,,0,0,0,,Quantum Electrodynamics,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.80,0:21:39.76,English,,0,0,0,,which is the theory that Feynman put the finishing touches on,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:44.00,English,,0,0,0,,is the most numerically precise physical theory ever invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.08,0:21:52.16,English,,0,0,0,,In recognition of this work, in 1965,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:54.88,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman was awarded a Nobel Prize for Physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,He shared it with two other physicists,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.40,0:22:01.16,English,,0,0,0,,Julian Schwinger and Sin-Itiro Tomonaga,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.16,0:22:03.52,English,,0,0,0,,who were also working on the same problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:12.24,English,,0,0,0,,Was it worth a Nobel Prize?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.24,0:22:15.72,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:19.80,English,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about the Nobel Prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.80,0:22:22.84,English,,0,0,0,,I don't understand what it's all about or what's worth what
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.84,0:22:25.48,English,,0,0,0,,and if the people in the Swedish Academy decide
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.48,0:22:28.72,English,,0,0,0,,that X, Y or Z wins the Nobel Prize, then so be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.72,0:22:31.56,English,,0,0,0,,I think it was entirely right and proper.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.56,0:22:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,It was one of the best-earned Nobel Prizes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:39.04,English,,0,0,0,,there ever was, I would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.04,0:22:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,I don't see that it makes any point that someone in the Swedish Academy
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.24,0:22:47.64,English,,0,0,0,,decides that this work is noble enough to receive a prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.64,0:22:49.24,English,,0,0,0,,I've already got the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.24,0:22:52.04,English,,0,0,0,,The prize is the pleasure of finding the thing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.04,0:22:53.64,English,,0,0,0,,The kick in the discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.64,0:22:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,The observation other people use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.28,0:22:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,Those are the real things!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.36,0:23:02.68,English,,0,0,0,,The honours are unreal to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.68,0:23:04.84,English,,0,0,0,,I don't believe in honours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.84,0:23:06.64,English,,0,0,0,,It bothers me. Honours bothers me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.64,0:23:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,Honours is epaulettes. Honours is uniforms.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.72,0:23:13.50,English,,0,0,0,,My Poppa brought me up this way. I can't stand it. It hurts me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.20,0:23:30.04,English,,0,0,0,,In 1959, on a trip to Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.04,0:23:33.08,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman met Yorkshire woman Gweneth Howarth.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.08,0:23:35.68,English,,0,0,0,,A year later, they were married.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.68,0:23:39.60,English,,0,0,0,,Back in California, now Professor of Physics at Caltech,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.60,0:23:42.44,English,,0,0,0,,Richard and Gweneth started a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,I got a kick, when I was a boy, of my father telling me things,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:50.96,English,,0,0,0,,so I tried to tell my son things that were interesting about the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.96,0:23:52.80,English,,0,0,0,,He was an excellent father.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.80,0:23:56.48,English,,0,0,0,,Always up to explaining things or do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.48,0:23:59.92,English,,0,0,0,,We would go on walks after dinner, my father and I,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.92,0:24:02.64,English,,0,0,0,,and talk about things and...and it was, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.64,0:24:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,it was wonderful and delightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.04,0:24:13.92,English,,0,0,0,,I asked him about things and he tried to explain them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.36,0:24:20.28,English,,0,0,0,,Physics and math and history and politics and science fiction
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.28,0:24:22.68,English,,0,0,0,,and life, the universe and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.32,0:24:28.60,English,,0,0,0,,I'm very lucky that I got to do that two or three times a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.60,0:24:30.40,English,,0,0,0,,Say, "Let's go for a walk." Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.72,0:24:36.40,English,,0,0,0,,Growing up with Richard Feynman as your dad was never dull,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.40,0:24:38.92,English,,0,0,0,,particularly if you were his teenage daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.52,0:24:45.56,English,,0,0,0,,My parents ordered a car, a van that we could all go camping in,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.56,0:24:48.44,English,,0,0,0,,and they had it painted,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.44,0:24:51.28,English,,0,0,0,,which was so...so odd,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.28,0:24:54.44,English,,0,0,0,,because they weren't like this at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.60,0:24:58.08,English,,0,0,0,,My father may have been immune to embarrassment,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.08,0:25:00.24,English,,0,0,0,,but I certainly was not!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.24,0:25:03.72,English,,0,0,0,,And they had, you know, the diagrams painted on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.72,0:25:06.56,English,,0,0,0,,So most people thought they were Indian designs,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.56,0:25:09.36,English,,0,0,0,,but I remember once we'd just gone to McDonalds
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.36,0:25:12.44,English,,0,0,0,,and we were in the parking lot and walking out to the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.44,0:25:15.80,English,,0,0,0,,and someone asked us, "Why is your van covered in Feynman diagrams?"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.80,0:25:18.32,English,,0,0,0,,And Mother says, "Because we're the Feynmans!"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.56,0:25:24.56,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's reputation as a communicator of science
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.56,0:25:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,was spreading around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.44,0:25:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,In the early 1960s,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.56,0:25:32.32,English,,0,0,0,,he began presenting lectures for the public, which were televised.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.84,0:25:42.72,English,,0,0,0,,APPLAUSE
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.36,0:25:52.52,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to discuss how we would look for a new law.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.52,0:25:55.32,English,,0,0,0,,In general, we look for a new law by the following process.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.32,0:25:57.32,English,,0,0,0,,First, we guess it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.32,0:25:58.92,English,,0,0,0,,LAUGHTER
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.92,0:26:01.44,English,,0,0,0,,Don't laugh. That's really true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.44,0:26:04.20,English,,0,0,0,,Then we compute the consequences of the guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.20,0:26:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,If it disagrees with the experiment...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.84,0:26:10.24,English,,0,0,0,,..it's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.24,0:26:13.48,English,,0,0,0,,In that simple statement is the key to science.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.48,0:26:16.24,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make a difference how beautiful your guess is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.24,0:26:18.64,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make a difference how smart you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.64,0:26:20.68,English,,0,0,0,,who made the guess, or what his name is.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.68,0:26:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,If it disagrees with the experiment, it's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.64,0:26:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,That's all there is to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.64,0:26:27.20,English,,0,0,0,,LAUGHTER
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.60,0:26:31.76,English,,0,0,0,,Caltech invited him to re-write the physics curriculum
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.76,0:26:34.12,English,,0,0,0,,for undergraduates. His new course,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.12,0:26:37.16,English,,0,0,0,,spanning the entire history of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.16,0:26:40.08,English,,0,0,0,,became known as 'The Feynman Lectures.'
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.08,0:26:45.48,English,,0,0,0,,All these lectures had a certain amount of excitement...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.48,0:26:49.44,English,,0,0,0,,and an element of what you might call
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.44,0:26:52.36,English,,0,0,0,,solid showbiz demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.36,0:26:54.64,English,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you're all familiar with the joke
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.64,0:26:57.68,English,,0,0,0,,about the fact that the average family in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.68,0:26:59.88,English,,0,0,0,,seems to have two-and-a-half children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.88,0:27:03.32,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that there's a half a child in any family, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.32,0:27:04.76,English,,0,0,0,,the children come in lumps!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.76,0:27:06.36,English,,0,0,0,,LAUGHTER
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.36,0:27:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,He was very visual. He told jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.32,0:27:14.00,English,,0,0,0,,He had a unique way of explaining things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.00,0:27:17.52,English,,0,0,0,,and sometimes that was a slight problem
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.52,0:27:21.40,English,,0,0,0,,because he was so engaging, you'd walk out of a lecture thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.40,0:27:23.52,English,,0,0,0,,"Well, that all made complete sense."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.52,0:27:27.72,English,,0,0,0,,But, of course, five minutes later, you couldn't really remember all the connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.72,0:27:30.96,English,,0,0,0,,You were just swept along by Feynman's personality,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.96,0:27:33.72,English,,0,0,0,,by his humour, by his analogies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.72,0:27:36.64,English,,0,0,0,,Graduate students started idolising him,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.64,0:27:42.20,English,,0,0,0,,but by the 1960s his course here at Caltech was very famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.88,0:27:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,Outside science, Feynman's interests were also flourishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.52,0:27:51.08,English,,0,0,0,,He'd become an accomplished bongo player.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.08,0:27:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,And he developed a love of painting and drawing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.76,0:27:55.96,English,,0,0,0,,based on a close friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.96,0:27:59.84,English,,0,0,0,,with renowned Californian artist, Jirayr Zorthian.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.84,0:28:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,"Jirayr", he said. "You don't know a thing about physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.68,0:28:08.28,English,,0,0,0,,"and I don't know a thing about art.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.28,0:28:11.56,English,,0,0,0,,“And yet we both admire Leonardo Da Vinci.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.56,0:28:16.04,English,,0,0,0,,“What do you say, we become two Leonardo da Vincis?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.04,0:28:20.40,English,,0,0,0,,He said, “One Sunday I will give you a day of physics
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.40,0:28:23.76,English,,0,0,0,,“and the following Sunday, you give me a day of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:28.04,English,,0,0,0,,When he started, he was absolutely an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.04,0:28:31.68,English,,0,0,0,,Just very, very...crude.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.32,0:28:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,He drew a picture of me when I was,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.96,0:28:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,when I was young and very fidgety,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.40,0:28:42.88,English,,0,0,0,,and, and it just has, you know he just has my, my head,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.88,0:28:48.12,English,,0,0,0,,some hair, and then, and then like my hands up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.12,0:28:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,so clearly I was kind of like, "Oh, I don't really want to do this."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.12,0:28:58.12,English,,0,0,0,,It's pure with his, um, that he can see the gesture.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.12,0:29:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,I think he maybe got a kick out of working with his hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.60,0:29:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,but particularly the pen and doing features of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.68,0:29:14.96,English,,0,0,0,,In the end, he became a very accomplished draftsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.20,0:29:22.20,English,,0,0,0,,So enthusiastic an art student was Feynman,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.20,0:29:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,that he took to spending time in Giannoni's, a strip bar in Pasadena.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.44,0:29:31.00,English,,0,0,0,,Here, he divided his attention between sketching the girls
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.00,0:29:33.64,English,,0,0,0,,and solving physics equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.68,0:29:38.32,English,,0,0,0,,Other physicists couldn't understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.32,0:29:43.20,English,,0,0,0,,And say, "You know, Feynman is supposed to be a physicist
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.20,0:29:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,"and he is a brilliant, brilliant physicist
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.04,0:29:52.76,English,,0,0,0,,"and we need his input very often in Caltech.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.76,0:29:57.00,English,,0,0,0,,"We need him to talk to us about physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.00,0:29:59.24,English,,0,0,0,,But what does he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.24,0:30:05.52,English,,0,0,0,,He goes off and spends all his time with go-go girls,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.52,0:30:08.80,English,,0,0,0,,bongo drummers and artists.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.80,0:30:11.56,English,,0,0,0,,He wastes so much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.56,0:30:15.28,English,,0,0,0,,on people 'I don't see  what they give him.'
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.28,0:30:20.64,English,,0,0,0,,'But I think that Feynman got a lot out of these people
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.64,0:30:24.80,English,,0,0,0,,'and it enriched his life.'
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.32,0:30:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,In the 1960s, Feynman took a sabbatical year.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.88,0:30:32.68,English,,0,0,0,,But instead of heading for a different physics department
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.68,0:30:36.20,English,,0,0,0,,the other side of the country, he simply crossed the Caltech campus
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.20,0:30:40.48,English,,0,0,0,,to study an area which had long fascinated him - viruses.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.48,0:30:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,During this time, he also became fascinated
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.04,0:30:46.76,English,,0,0,0,,by the social structure of ants
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.76,0:30:50.88,English,,0,0,0,,and enthralled by the potential applications of nanotechnology.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.48,0:30:58.96,English,,0,0,0,,In the long term of what he wanted to do this year and next year,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.96,0:31:01.52,English,,0,0,0,,he would think about...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.52,0:31:04.00,English,,0,0,0,,figuring out some secret of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.00,0:31:07.08,English,,0,0,0,,but in terms of day-to-day or hour-to-hour
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.08,0:31:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,he was always guided by, what seemed interesting and fun
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.28,0:31:16.12,English,,0,0,0,,and just sort of an intuition for the right thing to work on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.04,0:31:21.52,English,,0,0,0,,In the early 1980s, his son Carl's budding career
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.52,0:31:25.76,English,,0,0,0,,in the emerging field of super computers proved irresistible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.76,0:31:31.04,English,,0,0,0,,He signed up for a summer job at Carl's start-up company in Boston.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.04,0:31:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,'We were a bunch of MIT students starting a company.'
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.68,0:31:37.32,English,,0,0,0,,So, the first day we start the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.32,0:31:40.72,English,,0,0,0,,literally, I get this knock on the door, I open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.72,0:31:45.40,English,,0,0,0,,And he showed up and he said, "Feynman reporting for duty, what should I do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.40,0:31:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,Salutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.52,0:31:52.00,English,,0,0,0,,I think, "Uh oh, I haven't figured out what I'll do with this guy!"
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.00,0:31:55.84,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, I've got a Nobel Prize winning great physicist...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.84,0:31:58.68,English,,0,0,0,,So, I've had a quick meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.68,0:32:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,and trying to come up with some project that was worthy of Feynman.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.56,0:32:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,So, some people said, "We want you to think about applications
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.88,0:32:08.04,English,,0,0,0,,"of our parallel computing."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.04,0:32:12.44,English,,0,0,0,,The application of parallel processing to quantum chromodynamics.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.44,0:32:16.72,English,,0,0,0,,He said, "No, come on, that's, that's nonsense, you know."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.72,0:32:18.96,English,,0,0,0,,"What do you really want me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:22.04,English,,0,0,0,,And, I said, "Well, actually, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.04,0:32:24.44,English,,0,0,0,,"we don't really have any pencils or paper..."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.44,0:32:26.92,English,,0,0,0,,He said, "Right, I'll go out and buy some!"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.92,0:32:31.12,English,,0,0,0,,So, his first duty was to go out and buy the stationery for the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.12,0:32:34.32,English,,0,0,0,,All the paper clips and pencils and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.32,0:32:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,That was his first assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.92,0:32:41.56,English,,0,0,0,,'Thinking Machines', as the company was called,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.56,0:32:43.76,English,,0,0,0,,would go on to become a major player
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.76,0:32:46.64,English,,0,0,0,,in the world of Parallel Super-computing,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.64,0:32:50.08,English,,0,0,0,,with Feynman applying his methods of shortening calculations,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.08,0:32:55.32,English,,0,0,0,,developed in the 1940s, to the new digital age.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.32,0:32:57.96,English,,0,0,0,,And as always, working with Feynman
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.96,0:33:00.80,English,,0,0,0,,was filled with welcome distractions.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.80,0:33:04.88,English,,0,0,0,,We both liked spaghetti, because it was easy to cook,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.88,0:33:10.32,English,,0,0,0,,and I ask him why it was that when you broke a piece of spaghetti
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.32,0:33:13.20,English,,0,0,0,,it often broke into three pieces, instead of two?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.20,0:33:15.96,English,,0,0,0,,You should try it, it really does.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.32,0:33:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,So, of course, he came up with a theory of it immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.96,0:33:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,but instead of being satisfied with it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.64,0:33:29.04,English,,0,0,0,,he constructed an experiment to see if the theory was true,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.04,0:33:32.60,English,,0,0,0,,which involved slowly moving the spaghetti off the end of the table
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.60,0:33:34.64,English,,0,0,0,,and breaking it at different lengths.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.64,0:33:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,And then, that theory was wrong and he came up with another theory
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:42.36,English,,0,0,0,,and then each theory would lead to another experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.36,0:33:45.32,English,,0,0,0,,By the time the evening was over, we had broken spaghetti
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.32,0:33:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,all over the place and we STILL didn't know why
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.52,0:33:50.72,English,,0,0,0,,spaghetti broke in three places.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.24,0:33:58.76,English,,0,0,0,,This playful curiosity coupled with the anti-authoritarian values,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.76,0:34:03.96,English,,0,0,0,,instilled by his father, frequently led Feynman down a mischievous path.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.80,0:34:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,He's just so funny and irreverent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.04,0:34:14.96,English,,0,0,0,,You have to kind of look at that picture a few minutes and think...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.96,0:34:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,"Oh my gosh, he's really, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.00,0:34:21.68,English,,0,0,0,,"Making nice little horns!"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.72,0:34:27.56,English,,0,0,0,,Important people. You know. "Oh yes, I think now would be a great time."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.00,0:34:33.04,English,,0,0,0,,He didn't need the external validation
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.04,0:34:35.52,English,,0,0,0,,of having everybody respecting him all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.52,0:34:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,because he respected himself, he knew he was an extraordinary person.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.12,0:34:41.56,English,,0,0,0,,And if he came off as kind of a doofus
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.56,0:34:44.92,English,,0,0,0,,to some guy that he doesn't know, it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.92,0:34:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,Because he knows inside that he's a man of substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.16,0:34:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,In 1984, Feynman collaborated with his friend, Ralph Leighton
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.80,0:34:59.84,English,,0,0,0,,on a humorous book of anecdotes from his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.16,0:35:06.32,English,,0,0,0,,'I opened the safes which contained all the secrets to the atomic bomb.'
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.20,0:35:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,It was kind of accidental how the books caught on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.92,0:35:16.52,English,,0,0,0,,The publisher released the first one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.52,0:35:20.28,English,,0,0,0,,Surely You're Joking, Mr Feynman, in January of 1985.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.28,0:35:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,And the edition was like 2,000 copies or some low number.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.44,0:35:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,And in January.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.56,0:35:35.36,English,,0,0,0,,I was thinking, January, the whole holiday season is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.36,0:35:38.60,English,,0,0,0,,who's going to buy a book in January?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:42.72,English,,0,0,0,,But people did buy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.72,0:35:47.20,English,,0,0,0,,And Surely You're Joking, Mr Feynman quickly became a best seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.20,0:35:49.08,English,,0,0,0,,It remains to this day,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.08,0:35:53.32,English,,0,0,0,,one of the biggest-selling science books of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.32,0:35:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,I do remember coming down one evening and seeing him
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.36,0:36:01.60,English,,0,0,0,,just, you know, giggling
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.60,0:36:05.24,English,,0,0,0,,and clearly enjoying the book that he was reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.24,0:36:08.84,English,,0,0,0,,And I sort of looked, you know, "What are you reading?"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.84,0:36:12.60,English,,0,0,0,,And he held up the book so I could see that it was his own,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.60,0:36:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,Surely You're Joking. And he said, "Ah, such a character."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.64,0:36:23.32,English,,0,0,0,,Freely admitting that, yes, he was laughing at his own history.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.56,0:36:27.60,English,,0,0,0,,The book vividly captured Feynman's world view,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.60,0:36:31.12,English,,0,0,0,,the sense of curiosity and fun guiding him through life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.36,0:36:35.84,English,,0,0,0,,It was an approach he communicated to an even bigger audience through
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.84,0:36:39.80,English,,0,0,0,,a series of BBC documentaries, broadcast around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.08,0:36:49.16,English,,0,0,0,,I have a friend who's an artist and he's sometimes taken a view,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.16,0:36:51.76,English,,0,0,0,,which I don't agree with very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.76,0:36:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,You hold up a flower and say, "Look how beautiful it is." And I'll agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.60,0:36:59.72,English,,0,0,0,,And he says, I, as an artist, can see how beautiful this is,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.72,0:37:01.32,English,,0,0,0,,but you, as a scientist,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.32,0:37:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,take this all apart and it becomes a dull thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.48,0:37:06.96,English,,0,0,0,,And I think that he's kind of nutty.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.96,0:37:10.88,English,,0,0,0,,First of all, the beauty that he sees is available to other people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.88,0:37:12.48,English,,0,0,0,,and to me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.48,0:37:16.00,English,,0,0,0,,I believe, although I may not be quite as refined aesthetically
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.00,0:37:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,as he is, that I can appreciate the beauty of the flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.12,0:37:23.84,English,,0,0,0,,At the same time, I see much more about the flower than he sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.84,0:37:27.32,English,,0,0,0,,I could imagine the cells in there, the complicated actions inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.32,0:37:28.96,English,,0,0,0,,which also have a beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.96,0:37:32.64,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's not just beauty at this dimension of one centimetre,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.64,0:37:36.28,English,,0,0,0,,there's also beauty at a smaller dimensions, the inner structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.28,0:37:38.24,English,,0,0,0,,Also the processes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.24,0:37:43.48,English,,0,0,0,,The fact that the colours and the flower are evolved in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.48,0:37:47.20,English,,0,0,0,,attract insects to pollinate it is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.20,0:37:50.24,English,,0,0,0,,It means that insects can see the colour.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.24,0:37:51.68,English,,0,0,0,,It adds a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.68,0:37:55.16,English,,0,0,0,,does this aesthetic sense also exist in the lower forms?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.16,0:37:57.36,English,,0,0,0,,Why is it aesthetic?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.36,0:38:03.16,English,,0,0,0,,All kinds of interesting questions, which a science knowledge only adds
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.16,0:38:07.40,English,,0,0,0,,to the excitement and mystery and the aura of a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.40,0:38:10.64,English,,0,0,0,,It only adds. I don't understand how it subtracts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.64,0:38:13.32,English,,0,0,0,,Most people only have a few stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.32,0:38:16.48,English,,0,0,0,,You and I might have three or four stories to tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.48,0:38:20.56,English,,0,0,0,,Some people have ten, and Feynman had hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.56,0:38:24.64,English,,0,0,0,,And Feynman was so mesmerizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.64,0:38:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,I think Chris Sykes in his documentaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.64,0:38:30.00,English,,0,0,0,,captured Feynman how he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.00,0:38:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,He takes enormous pleasure in finding out about things
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.16,0:38:35.80,English,,0,0,0,,and exploring life and everything it has to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.80,0:38:38.84,English,,0,0,0,,More than that, he takes tremendous pleasure in telling you about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.84,0:38:41.04,English,,0,0,0,,I think he was pleased with how it worked out,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.04,0:38:44.68,English,,0,0,0,,that he was able to communicate with so many people,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.68,0:38:47.40,English,,0,0,0,,sort of his view of the world and of nature and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.40,0:38:53.24,English,,0,0,0,,When I was a student at Caltech, I went up to Feynman's door
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.24,0:38:56.88,English,,0,0,0,,and knocked on it and a door opened and I explained
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.88,0:38:59.44,English,,0,0,0,,that my mother had watched his programme about him,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.44,0:39:02.60,English,,0,0,0,,thought he was interesting, she had no science background,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.60,0:39:04.88,English,,0,0,0,,and I said, "Do you think you could write to her
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.88,0:39:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,"because maybe I'll have a better chance of teaching her physics?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.08,0:39:11.36,English,,0,0,0,,And Feynman did write to her. He wrote a letter in which he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.36,0:39:16.08,English,,0,0,0,,"Dear Mrs Chown. Ignore your son's attempts to teach you physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.08,0:39:20.88,English,,0,0,0,,"Physics is not the most important thing. Love is."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.88,0:39:22.80,English,,0,0,0,,So it kind of backfired.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.80,0:39:25.32,English,,0,0,0,,I got the greatest living physicist at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.32,0:39:27.96,English,,0,0,0,,telling my mother that physics isn't important.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.96,0:39:29.88,English,,0,0,0,,That love was the important thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.96,0:39:45.04,English,,0,0,0,,Through his films and books, Feynman had touched the lives of millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.04,0:39:48.56,English,,0,0,0,,Yet there was something all this success
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.56,0:39:50.52,English,,0,0,0,,and recognition couldn't alter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:56.24,English,,0,0,0,,I did a lot of running and Feynman thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.24,0:40:00.52,English,,0,0,0,,gee, that's a healthy thing to do, so he started running too.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.52,0:40:05.16,English,,0,0,0,,And when you start running regularly, you lose weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.16,0:40:09.88,English,,0,0,0,,And Feynman suddenly noticed that one side kind of bulged out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.28,0:40:14.68,English,,0,0,0,,They discovered a big mass in his abdomen.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.68,0:40:16.04,English,,0,0,0,,He came home and reported,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.04,0:40:18.76,English,,0,0,0,,"It's the size of a football. It's consumed one whole kidney."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.76,0:40:21.00,English,,0,0,0,,And he says, "Well, I went to the medical library
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.00,0:40:22.92,English,,0,0,0,,"and I looked things up and I figure
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.92,0:40:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,"it's about a 30% chance it'll kill me."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.64,0:40:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,So, you know, not the kind of thing you want to hear from your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.12,0:40:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,But exactly the kind of thing he would say.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.00,0:40:36.16,English,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.16,0:40:39.88,English,,0,0,0,,He sort of quit working at that point, because, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.88,0:40:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,surgery and chemotherapy and so on, it's a full time job.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.56,0:40:47.84,English,,0,0,0,,One day his secretary Helen Tuck called me up
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.84,0:40:50.88,English,,0,0,0,,to tell me that Dick had cancer and that he was going to the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.88,0:40:52.72,English,,0,0,0,,for an operation the following Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.72,0:40:55.16,English,,0,0,0,,It was a very dangerous operation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.16,0:40:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,and it was not assured that he would survive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.88,0:41:01.80,English,,0,0,0,,I promised not to tell anyone and he didn't know that I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.80,0:41:06.08,English,,0,0,0,,And I told him that somebody had found an apparent error
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.08,0:41:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,in a calculation that we had done and published together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.32,0:41:12.32,English,,0,0,0,,And so on Monday morning we met in my office
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.32,0:41:17.44,English,,0,0,0,,and he sat down and started working, and he was consumed by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.44,0:41:21.32,English,,0,0,0,,All his energy and attention was devoted to solving this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.32,0:41:23.44,English,,0,0,0,,And we worked on it all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.44,0:41:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,And finally at six o'clock in the evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.80,0:41:28.96,English,,0,0,0,,we decided the problem was intractable, it couldn't be solved,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.96,0:41:31.28,English,,0,0,0,,we couldn't figure out what the answer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.28,0:41:33.32,English,,0,0,0,,And we gave up and went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.32,0:41:37.32,English,,0,0,0,,Two hours later, he called me at home to say he'd solved the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.32,0:41:40.80,English,,0,0,0,,He hadn't been able to give up, and stop working on it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.80,0:41:42.52,English,,0,0,0,,and finally he'd found the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.52,0:41:45.72,English,,0,0,0,,He dictated the solution to me over the phone, told me what it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.72,0:41:48.32,English,,0,0,0,,and he was exhilarated, absolutely walking on air.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.56,0:41:53.00,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman would recover from this first operation for cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.00,0:41:56.00,English,,0,0,0,,But the disease would never completely go away,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.00,0:41:59.48,English,,0,0,0,,and he would always be living under its shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.80,0:42:14.12,English,,0,0,0,,'We have main engine start. Four, three, two, one. And lift off.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.12,0:42:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,'Lift off of the 25th space shuttle mission
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.36,0:42:20.44,English,,0,0,0,,'and it has cleared the tower.'
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.44,0:42:23.00,English,,0,0,0,,'Challenger go with roll programme.'
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.00,0:42:25.04,English,,0,0,0,,'Roger. Roll, Challenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.04,0:42:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,'Good roll, programme.'
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.64,0:42:33.68,English,,0,0,0,,In January 1986, NASA launched its 25th space shuttle mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.68,0:42:37.96,English,,0,0,0,,It symbolized a new era of space flight by adding a school teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.96,0:42:40.88,English,,0,0,0,,called Christa McAuliffe to the crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.88,0:42:44.00,English,,0,0,0,,'65 final. Thank you.'
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.60,0:42:47.60,English,,0,0,0,,'Challenger. Go with throttle up.'
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.00,0:42:54.96,English,,0,0,0,,I was in social studies and I think we were taking a test and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.96,0:42:58.44,English,,0,0,0,,the teacher came in and said, "We've had a horrible accident."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.68,0:43:08.16,English,,0,0,0,,'Flight controllers here looking very carefully at the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.16,0:43:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,'We have no down link.'
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.68,0:43:14.00,English,,0,0,0,,And then coming home, and my parents had already seen it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.00,0:43:17.04,English,,0,0,0,,which was unusual because they didn't really watch TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.04,0:43:20.04,English,,0,0,0,,'Watch your data carefully.'
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.04,0:43:22.80,English,,0,0,0,,'Take hard copies of all of your displays.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.80,0:43:25.80,English,,0,0,0,,'Make sure you protect any data source you have.'
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.80,0:43:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,The loss of their space shuttle and its crew of seven, live on TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.12,0:43:34.24,English,,0,0,0,,shocked America. The country was thrown into mourning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.08,0:43:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,Our nation's loss is first a profound personal loss
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.84,0:43:42.80,English,,0,0,0,,to the family and the friends and the loved ones
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.80,0:43:45.36,English,,0,0,0,,of our shuttle astronauts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.36,0:43:49.32,English,,0,0,0,,But there was one question everyone wanted an answer to -
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.32,0:43:51.20,English,,0,0,0,,what had gone wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.64,0:43:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,A Presidential Commission was hastily put together to find out,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.68,0:44:00.16,English,,0,0,0,,but it was comprised largely of space industry insiders
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.16,0:44:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,with close ties to NASA.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.76,0:44:08.72,English,,0,0,0,,Someone independent with unimpeachable scientific credentials was needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.72,0:44:12.76,English,,0,0,0,,I have a policy practically of never going near Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.76,0:44:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,And I called up various friends of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.20,0:44:18.48,English,,0,0,0,,who were connected to the space programme one way or the other
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.48,0:44:20.92,English,,0,0,0,,and tried to ask them if they didn't see
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.92,0:44:24.28,English,,0,0,0,,whether I should go or somebody else could do it just as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.28,0:44:26.36,English,,0,0,0,,His friends were, "Dick, you got to go
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.36,0:44:29.84,English,,0,0,0,,"cos you're the only guy who can cut through the bullshit!"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:32.04,English,,0,0,0,,He asked me what I thought he should do
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.04,0:44:35.28,English,,0,0,0,,so I just asked him, "Do you think it's an important problem?"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.28,0:44:36.72,English,,0,0,0,,And he said, yes he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.72,0:44:38.88,English,,0,0,0,,I said, "Do you think you can make a difference?"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.88,0:44:41.84,English,,0,0,0,,And he said, after a while, he said, "Well, yeah, probably can."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.84,0:44:43.32,English,,0,0,0,,I didn't say another word.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.32,0:44:46.60,English,,0,0,0,,And after a few minutes hesitation he said, "To hell with you, Hibbs,"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.60,0:44:47.88,English,,0,0,0,,and hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.76,0:44:54.72,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman broke his policy and within days of the accident
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.72,0:44:57.40,English,,0,0,0,,he had joined the inquiry in Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.96,0:45:02.92,English,,0,0,0,,The investigation was led by William Rogers,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.92,0:45:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,an ex-Secretary of State and the ultimate Washington insider.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.92,0:45:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,His formal, bureaucratic approach was
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.68,0:45:14.08,English,,0,0,0,,the polar opposite of the freewheeling maverick professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.72,0:45:18.64,English,,0,0,0,,Mr Rogers, he knew nothing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.64,0:45:22.84,English,,0,0,0,,I had been on accident boards before and I took the opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.84,0:45:25.40,English,,0,0,0,,I said "Hey, I just did one of these investigations,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.40,0:45:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,"would you like to see it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.44,0:45:29.04,English,,0,0,0,,And I think reluctantly Rogers said
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.04,0:45:30.64,English,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, OK, you can show it to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.64,0:45:32.76,English,,0,0,0,,"but we're not going to do it that way."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.76,0:45:35.80,English,,0,0,0,,And so I went through this very logical step-by-step process of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.80,0:45:39.48,English,,0,0,0,,of how you investigate a space accident and Rogers said,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.48,0:45:42.12,English,,0,0,0,,"No, we don't have the technical capability to do that."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.12,0:45:44.08,English,,0,0,0,,And that's when Feynman butted in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.08,0:45:46.80,English,,0,0,0,,He said, "No, I like that. I think that's a smart way to go."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.20,0:45:50.28,English,,0,0,0,,For Feynman and the chairman,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.28,0:45:53.28,English,,0,0,0,,it was the beginning of a poor relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.28,0:45:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,but for the professor and the Air Force General,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.16,0:45:59.20,English,,0,0,0,,it was the start of a close friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.20,0:46:01.84,English,,0,0,0,,And he just was the smartest guy in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.84,0:46:06.28,English,,0,0,0,,And he had a reputation for integrity, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.28,0:46:09.16,English,,0,0,0,,he was the most honest guy in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.68,0:46:15.12,English,,0,0,0,,He didn't accept something unless he really could prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.88,0:46:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,The two men began touring the US,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.16,0:46:24.08,English,,0,0,0,,visiting NASA sites where the shuttle was made,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.08,0:46:27.00,English,,0,0,0,,questioning the engineers and managers.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.44,0:46:31.48,English,,0,0,0,,In the process of speaking to the engineers, he realised,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:34.36,English,,0,0,0,,"Wow, some of them won't talk to me right now cos
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.36,0:46:37.00,English,,0,0,0,,"the managers are in the room," you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.00,0:46:40.08,English,,0,0,0,,It wasn't simply a technical puzzle,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.08,0:46:44.00,English,,0,0,0,,there was a human puzzle going on too.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.00,0:46:46.72,English,,0,0,0,,Writing home to Michelle and Gweneth,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.72,0:46:50.56,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman expressed his frustration and excitement
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.56,0:46:52.28,English,,0,0,0,,at his hunt for the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.80,0:46:56.04,English,,0,0,0,,'Dearest Gweneth and Michelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.04,0:46:59.28,English,,0,0,0,,'This is the first time I have had time to write to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.28,0:47:03.20,English,,0,0,0,,'I already smell certain rats that I will not forget because I just
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.20,0:47:07.44,English,,0,0,0,,'love the smell of rats, for it is the spore of exciting adventure.'
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.44,0:47:14.76,English,,0,0,0,,But there was a problem, NASA managers didn't want to reveal
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.76,0:47:17.56,English,,0,0,0,,the full extent of their knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.84,0:47:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,The result was a smokescreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.76,0:47:28.36,English,,0,0,0,,NASA wanted to control everything that they gave
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.36,0:47:32.36,English,,0,0,0,,to the Commission and actually withheld things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.36,0:47:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,They didn't lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.80,0:47:37.28,English,,0,0,0,,but they certainly didn't go around blabbing the truth either.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.68,0:47:41.24,English,,0,0,0,,What Feynman didn't know was that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.24,0:47:44.80,English,,0,0,0,,General Kutyna had a secret source inside NASA.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.80,0:47:48.68,English,,0,0,0,,Sally Ride was America's first woman in space
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.68,0:47:51.48,English,,0,0,0,,and another Commission member.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.48,0:47:55.40,English,,0,0,0,,She privately told the general that NASA had long had doubts
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.40,0:47:57.04,English,,0,0,0,,about how the rubber O-rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.04,0:48:00.08,English,,0,0,0,,the seals in the shuttle's solid rocket boosters,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.08,0:48:02.00,English,,0,0,0,,worked in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.00,0:48:06.12,English,,0,0,0,,The temperature on the morning of the launch had been below freezing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.12,0:48:09.40,English,,0,0,0,,The general needed to get this information to Feynman
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.40,0:48:11.60,English,,0,0,0,,without compromising his source.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.00,0:48:18.32,English,,0,0,0,,The chance came after supper one evening at Kutyna's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.32,0:48:21.08,English,,0,0,0,,The general restored classic cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.08,0:48:24.04,English,,0,0,0,,I took him out in the garage to show him the car
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.04,0:48:26.88,English,,0,0,0,,and Feynman really isn't interested in cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.88,0:48:30.92,English,,0,0,0,,So we walked around the car and I showed him the interior
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.92,0:48:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,and I showed him where the engine was.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.36,0:48:35.44,English,,0,0,0,,And Feynman looked at my work bench
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.44,0:48:38.16,English,,0,0,0,,and he sees a couple of carburettors out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.16,0:48:40.92,English,,0,0,0,,And he says, "Kutyna, what are those carburettors?"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.92,0:48:44.96,English,,0,0,0,,And I said, "Oh, they're from the Opal and I keep one put together
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.96,0:48:47.40,English,,0,0,0,,"and then one I take apart and clean."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.40,0:48:49.72,English,,0,0,0,,And then the thought came to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.72,0:48:54.88,English,,0,0,0,,I needed to get the idea of cold and O-rings and leakage across.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:48:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,I said, "You know, Professor, these doggone carburettors have O-rings
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.36,0:49:01.08,English,,0,0,0,,"and they leak when they're cold."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.44,0:49:07.92,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman had his answer and he also had an inspired idea
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:11.56,English,,0,0,0,,about how to convey it to the world's press.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.00,0:49:19.36,English,,0,0,0,,From that and the various things that you told me
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.36,0:49:22.60,English,,0,0,0,,about the need for resilience and the lack of resilience...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.60,0:49:25.36,English,,0,0,0,,When the Commission next met, he began questioning
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.36,0:49:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,senior engineers about the effect of cold on the O-rings
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.84,0:49:31.32,English,,0,0,0,,on the morning of the launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.32,0:49:33.44,English,,0,0,0,,Their replies were evasive,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.44,0:49:36.72,English,,0,0,0,,denying that temperature could have had an effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.84,0:49:43.64,English,,0,0,0,,Before the event, from information that was available
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.64,0:49:45.88,English,,0,0,0,,and the understanding that was available,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.88,0:49:48.76,English,,0,0,0,,was it fully appreciated everywhere that this seal
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.76,0:49:53.40,English,,0,0,0,,would become unsatisfactory at some temperature?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.40,0:49:58.28,English,,0,0,0,,And was there some sort of a suggestion of a temperature at which
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.28,0:50:01.12,English,,0,0,0,,the SR...the SRB I guess you call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.12,0:50:04.00,English,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right...Shouldn't be run?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.00,0:50:07.40,English,,0,0,0,,It was the judgment that under the conditions that we would see
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.40,0:50:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,on launch day, given the configuration that we ran,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.68,0:50:13.16,English,,0,0,0,,that the seal would function at that temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.16,0:50:14.92,English,,0,0,0,,That was the final judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.92,0:50:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,It was Feynman's chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.36,0:50:20.92,English,,0,0,0,,He decided to use the power of a classic science demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.04,0:50:25.92,English,,0,0,0,,During the hearings, they had that actual O-ring joint
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.92,0:50:27.92,English,,0,0,0,,and were passing it up the rows.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.92,0:50:29.64,English,,0,0,0,,It goes to Feynman.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.64,0:50:34.84,English,,0,0,0,,I'm sitting to his left and I hand it to him and he puts it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.84,0:50:39.92,English,,0,0,0,,And then he goes into his pocket and pulls out the pliers and the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.92,0:50:44.16,English,,0,0,0,,hose clamp and the screwdriver, and takes the joint apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.16,0:50:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,Pulls out the piece of rubber O-ring, puts the clamp on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.04,0:50:49.84,English,,0,0,0,,then I know what he's going to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.84,0:50:54.12,English,,0,0,0,,He sees the ice water and he swears it was just kind of an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.12,0:50:58.00,English,,0,0,0,,He got this idea, "Wait a minute, I know I know how
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.00,0:51:02.04,English,,0,0,0,,"I can get data on how rubber is when it's cold."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.04,0:51:07.24,English,,0,0,0,,He clamped a piece of rubber and put it in a beaker full of ice water.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.24,0:51:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,I took this stuff that I got out of your seal and I put it in ice water.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.84,0:51:16.68,English,,0,0,0,,And I discovered that when you put some pressure on it for a while
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.68,0:51:20.32,English,,0,0,0,,and then undo it, it maintains, it doesn't stretch back,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.32,0:51:22.76,English,,0,0,0,,it stays the same dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.76,0:51:25.28,English,,0,0,0,,In other words, for a few seconds at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.28,0:51:28.48,English,,0,0,0,,and more seconds than that, there's no resilience in this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.48,0:51:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,particular material when it's at a temperature of 32 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.16,0:51:37.32,English,,0,0,0,,I believe that has some significance for our problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.88,0:51:46.36,English,,0,0,0,,The O-rings, which were supposed to create a seal
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.36,0:51:50.60,English,,0,0,0,,around the solid boosters, had got so cold they'd lost their ability
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.60,0:51:55.44,English,,0,0,0,,to flex and to fill the gap between the boosters.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.32,0:52:01.76,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why the fuel had leaked and the shuttle had exploded.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.76,0:52:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman had nailed, once and for all,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.52,0:52:06.96,English,,0,0,0,,that the cold could have been the cause
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.96,0:52:10.56,English,,0,0,0,,of the shuttle's failure just 73 seconds after launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.56,0:52:14.36,English,,0,0,0,,It really was a turning point in the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.36,0:52:15.76,English,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.20,0:52:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,In the summer of 1986, the Commission's report was submitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.08,0:52:25.72,English,,0,0,0,,In its appendix, Feynman added a stark reminder
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.72,0:52:28.16,English,,0,0,0,,about the limits of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.16,0:52:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,His last recommendation I think
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.44,0:52:32.84,English,,0,0,0,,really summed it up in one simple paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.72,0:52:36.92,English,,0,0,0,,"For a successful technology,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.92,0:52:41.80,English,,0,0,0,,"reality must take precedence over public relations,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.80,0:52:43.76,English,,0,0,0,,"for nature cannot be fooled."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.40,0:52:54.68,English,,0,0,0,,I remember, it was very hard on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.68,0:52:58.84,English,,0,0,0,,He was just exhausted. He came over, he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.84,0:53:03.92,English,,0,0,0,,"I came over to tell you that my cancer's come back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.76,0:53:08.12,English,,0,0,0,,"Doesn't look too good."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.12,0:53:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,So I don't know what we talked about and I don't know how
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.28,0:53:13.80,English,,0,0,0,,I got off on the subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.80,0:53:18.80,English,,0,0,0,,I said, "I've been thinking about an invariant in turbulent flow."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.80,0:53:20.84,English,,0,0,0,,He said, "What do you mean?"
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.84,0:53:24.04,English,,0,0,0,,I explained a little bit what it was all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.04,0:53:25.84,English,,0,0,0,,The invariant, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.84,0:53:29.92,English,,0,0,0,,I said, "Well under these, such and such conditions."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:31.96,English,,0,0,0,,And he says, "Let's see."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.96,0:53:34.20,English,,0,0,0,,So I had a notebook there.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.20,0:53:39.28,English,,0,0,0,,He took the notebook and he started, he wrote it all down step by step.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.28,0:53:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,I think it took 13 steps to get to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.36,0:53:47.40,English,,0,0,0,,He says, "Yes, that's true, it is an invariant."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.20,0:53:53.28,English,,0,0,0,,Then he says, "You got me thinking about physics again.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.28,0:53:55.12,English,,0,0,0,,"I can go home now."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.16,0:54:02.84,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman went into hospital for the last time in February 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.84,0:54:05.88,English,,0,0,0,,His kidneys were failing and he decided
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.88,0:54:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,he didn't want to go through with dialysis to prolong his suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.96,0:54:15.84,English,,0,0,0,,I still sort of thought, "No, this isn't the way it is."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.84,0:54:19.88,English,,0,0,0,,But he was able to handle a lot of physical difficulties
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.88,0:54:22.28,English,,0,0,0,,as long as his mind was sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.28,0:54:27.44,English,,0,0,0,,When a person is dying, their hands move a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.44,0:54:33.52,English,,0,0,0,,And the nurse who was there says that he's not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.52,0:54:37.76,English,,0,0,0,,trying to communicate,that's just natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.16,0:54:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,And he raised his hands like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.32,0:54:53.36,English,,0,0,0,,And he went like this, which, if you know it, is the symbol that
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.36,0:54:57.32,English,,0,0,0,,a magician gives when he's going to do a trick. OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.32,0:54:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,And he went...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.16,0:55:08.68,English,,0,0,0,,He was communicating, again, of his observations of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.68,0:55:11.72,English,,0,0,0,,The doctors were wrong, he could hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.72,0:55:14.92,English,,0,0,0,,He could move if he tried hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.92,0:55:19.60,English,,0,0,0,,And understand... He could hear and understand what was being said.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.60,0:55:21.40,English,,0,0,0,,And those were his last words.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.08,0:55:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,Richard Feynman died on the 15th February 1988
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.56,0:55:32.32,English,,0,0,0,,in hospital in Los Angeles at the age of just 69.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.08,0:55:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,When I took my last walk with Richard Feynman, he was telling me
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.12,0:55:44.20,English,,0,0,0,,a bunch of funny stories, but I realised the message behind
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.20,0:55:49.52,English,,0,0,0,,the stories was that he was about to die of cancer and I got very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.32,0:55:55.28,English,,0,0,0,,And he noticed it and he asked me, "What's wrong?"
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.28,0:55:59.60,English,,0,0,0,,And I said, "I'm sad because I'm realising that you're about to die."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.24,0:56:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,And he said, "Yeah, that bugs me sometimes too.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.88,0:56:12.04,English,,0,0,0,,"But not as much as you'd think," he said, "because you realise
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.04,0:56:17.48,English,,0,0,0,,"that at some point in your life, you've told a lot of stories
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.48,0:56:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,"and those stories are going to stay around even after you're gone."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.16,0:56:26.48,English,,0,0,0,,Today, over 25 years since his death,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.48,0:56:30.92,English,,0,0,0,,Feynman's prophecy has more truth than he could ever have imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.92,0:56:34.36,English,,0,0,0,,Through an invention that hadn't been created when he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.36,0:56:36.56,English,,0,0,0,,his stories do live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.80,0:56:41.40,English,,0,0,0,,Because through their reimagining on the World Wide Web,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.40,0:56:45.84,English,,0,0,0,,a new generation is discovering the delights of time with Feynman.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.88,0:56:54.16,English,,0,0,0,,It's fantastic to just be able to Google Feynman, Richard Feynman,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.16,0:56:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,you know, any kind of variation and there it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.36,0:57:04.20,English,,0,0,0,,You have a lot of stuff out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.20,0:57:08.88,English,,0,0,0,,I see my father referenced in popular culture a lot more now
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.88,0:57:10.32,English,,0,0,0,,than when he was alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.24,0:57:18.96,English,,0,0,0,,I have a friend who's an artist and he's sometimes taken a view,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.96,0:57:21.44,English,,0,0,0,,which I don't agree with very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.44,0:57:25.64,English,,0,0,0,,You hold up a flower and say, "Look how beautiful it is." And I'll agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.64,0:57:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,And he says, I, as an artist, can see how beautiful this is,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.56,0:57:33.04,English,,0,0,0,,but you, as a scientist, take this all apart and it becomes a dull thing
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.04,0:57:35.12,English,,0,0,0,,and I think that he's kind of nutty.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.36,0:57:40.88,English,,0,0,0,,You wonder what Feynman would have made of the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.88,0:57:43.88,English,,0,0,0,,And I think he would really, really like the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.88,0:57:50.28,English,,0,0,0,,that he's spread all over the world in clips, short and long,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.28,0:57:54.20,English,,0,0,0,,on the internet, for maybe all time. I think he'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.20,0:57:56.64,English,,0,0,0,,You know, you just touch it like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.64,0:57:57.96,English,,0,0,0,,FEYNMAN'S VOICE
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.96,0:58:00.88,English,,0,0,0,,..and you bring his voice right back, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.88,0:58:03.92,English,,0,0,0,,'"The whole universe is in a glass of wine."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.92,0:58:07.80,English,,0,0,0,,'I don't think we'll ever know in what sense he meant that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.80,0:58:09.40,English,,0,0,0,,LAUGHTER
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.40,0:58:12.24,English,,0,0,0,,'For the poets don't like to be understood.'
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.88,0:58:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,I know what I'll remember him for.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.96,0:58:21.84,English,,0,0,0,,For being a good brother and a good person.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.88,0:58:27.76,English,,0,0,0,,He wasn't just the scientist, he wasn't just the artist,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.76,0:58:29.52,English,,0,0,0,,he wasn't just the educator.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.52,0:58:32.20,English,,0,0,0,,He was physics with a human face, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.20,0:58:35.04,English,,0,0,0,,He showed that in order to be a top-ranked physicist
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.04,0:58:36.72,English,,0,0,0,,you can still be a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.72,0:58:39.64,English,,0,0,0,,I think that's a very important legacy to people
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.64,0:58:41.20,English,,0,0,0,,who want to do science.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.20,0:58:43.48,English,,0,0,0,,It's a human endeavour and he showed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.12,0:58:52.88,English,,0,0,0,,Has Richard Feynman inspired you to follow your own path in life?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.88,0:58:57.20,English,,0,0,0,,Join The Open University to explore your options and find out more
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.20,0:59:00.60,English,,0,0,0,,about how he revolutionised the face of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.60,0:59:02.80,English,,0,0,0,,Go to:
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.28,0:59:07.48,English,,0,0,0,,And follow the links to The Open University.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.32,0:59:25.36,English,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by Red Bee Media Ltd
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.20,0:00:10.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理查德·费曼是20世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.24,0:00:12.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最杰出的科学家之一
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.16,0:00:14.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为一个聪明的物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:17.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在物理学方面开创了一个全新的领域
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.64,0:00:20.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他发现了一条新的自然规律，只有极少数人知道
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.88,0:00:25.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是有史以来数值上最精确的物理理论
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.16,0:00:29.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，他却轻视通过自己的努力获得的诺贝尔奖
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.60,0:00:31.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我已经得到了奖品
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.44,0:00:33.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,奖品就是发现这件事物的喜悦
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.88,0:00:35.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发现的时候就是中奖的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.32,0:00:38.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼的才华帮着重塑了历史
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:41.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在年轻的时候，他参与建造了原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.56,0:00:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结束了第二次世界大战
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.76,0:00:47.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可是，纵观他的一生，费曼拒绝权威
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.08,0:00:48.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,拒绝顺从
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.92,0:00:51.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,宁可取而代之地顺从自己的热情--
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.96,0:00:54.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从玩邦哥鼓到生物学
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.00,0:00:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从写诗到绘画
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:58.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从计算机到开保险箱
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.40,0:01:01.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼的魅力广为人知
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.12,0:01:04.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他去世前的日子里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.64,0:01:08.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为一个持不同观点的调查员\N调查挑战者号航天飞机遇难事故
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.36,0:01:10.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他面对华盛顿机构
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.96,0:01:13.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,去揭露真相，到底是什么原因导致的事故
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.92,0:01:16.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一块我取自密封舱的垫圈
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.96,0:01:18.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后我把它放进冰水里
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:22.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,特别是，费曼对待生活具有感染力的热情
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.52,0:01:25.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吸引了成千上万的读者和观众
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.28,0:01:28.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼成了一个表演者，几乎一生都在表演
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.68,0:01:31.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他走进任何一个房间，所有人的目光都会聚集到他身上
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.92,0:01:33.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是被关注的焦点
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.80,0:01:38.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,电子的行为在这一方面和质子是一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.48,0:01:43.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是说，它们都是扭曲的，但却是用同一个方式
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.40,0:01:47.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本片通过他自己的话，和最了解他的人
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.04,0:01:51.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,讲述一个在科学史上最有魅力的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,传播者的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.12,0:01:57.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是你得停下来，去思考事物的复杂性
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:01.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不可思议的大自然的本质
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.56,0:02:24.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我母亲怀了第一胎的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.28,0:02:27.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的父亲就说，“如果是个男孩”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:29.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我想让他成为一个科学家”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.28,0:02:36.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理查德·菲利普·费曼1918年9月11日出生
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.04,0:02:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在大萧条时期
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:41.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,工薪阶层的父母住在纽约的市郊
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.68,0:02:46.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使当我还是个孩子的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.12,0:02:48.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,爸爸过去经常让我坐在他的膝盖上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.36,0:02:51.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,念不列颠百科全书给我听
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:55.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他也会读，说，关于恐龙的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.68,0:02:57.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他会这样说比如
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.48,0:03:00.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“这个东西有25英尺高”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.96,0:03:03.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“它的头有6英尺宽”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:08.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，他总是停下来说，“让我们看看那意味着什么”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.12,0:03:11.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“那就意味着如果它站在我们家的前院”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.20,0:03:14.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“它就高的足以把它的头伸进窗户里来”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.56,0:03:17.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“但并不完全，因为头有点过宽了”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.76,0:03:20.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样思考非常令人兴奋和感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.08,0:03:23.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有这样巨大的动物
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.08,0:03:25.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它们都灭绝了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.00,0:03:27.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且在当时，没有人知道原因
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.76,0:03:31.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是我父亲教育我的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.52,0:03:37.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,十岁的时候，理查德自己已经有了一个家庭科学实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.24,0:03:39.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里他改装过旧的收音机
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.32,0:03:41.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,试验过物理原理
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:46.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他雇用我，一周4美分
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为他的试验助手
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:51.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让他的朋友惊奇不已
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.92,0:03:54.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你知道，那有个冒火花的间隙
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.16,0:03:55.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有电压在上面
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:03:59.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你把你的手指放到中间
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.48,0:04:01.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就会被电一下
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.64,0:04:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是我的工作，作为我的4美分薪水
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.52,0:04:09.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把我的手指放到火花间隙为了让他的朋友吃惊
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.36,0:04:14.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们的父亲，梅尔维尔·费曼
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.88,0:04:17.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在一家生产军服的公司工作
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.84,0:04:22.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种暴露在军队下的生活导致了他强烈地反对权威
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.12,0:04:24.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是他灌输给他儿子的价值观
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.08,0:04:29.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我父亲教给我的一件事情就是不要尊重权威
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.12,0:04:34.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他打开一份报纸，纽约时报，图上可能印着一个将军
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.12,0:04:36.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他就会说“看看，现在这些人”他说
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.72,0:04:39.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“这里有一个人站着而其他人都在鞠躬”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.68,0:04:42.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“那么，这里有区别吗？为什么他们都要向他鞠躬？”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.36,0:04:44.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“只是因为他的名声和他的地位”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.52,0:04:45.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“因为他的军服”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.80,0:04:48.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“而不是因为他做了什么特别的事情”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.72,0:04:56.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,17岁那年，费曼赢得了在纽约的数学竞赛
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.12,0:04:58.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随后人们就知道了，在数学学科里
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.20,0:05:00.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他具有极大的天赋
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.84,0:05:04.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1935，他获得了一个名额
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.24,0:05:08.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到麻省理工学院（MIT）就读
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.72,0:05:11.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是第一次出门在外
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.24,0:05:14.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他想念的不光是他的家人
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.64,0:05:18.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她非常漂亮
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:20.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,艾琳•格林鲍姆
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:23.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,沙滩上最美的女孩
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.36,0:05:29.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她有一对迷人的酒窝和长到腰的头发，当她解开发带时
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.04,0:05:32.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哦，我们很爱她
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.48,0:05:35.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们还没有正式订婚，她才15岁
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:37.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她很甜美
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:40.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们都很爱她，她也很爱我们大家
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.88,0:05:47.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从麻省毕业，费曼转到了普林斯顿
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.56,0:05:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在数学科目和物理入学考试取得满分---
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:52.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个空前绝后的成绩
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.20,0:05:59.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是回到家，事情就没那么完美了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.72,0:06:05.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,全家出发去度春假
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.76,0:06:08.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带着艾琳
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.20,0:06:10.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们一起游泳
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:14.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后我的父亲看见了艾琳脖子上的肿块
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:17.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后对她说“那是什么？”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:20.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她说不知道，但她去看了医生
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:23.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,得知那是肺结核
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:27.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们都感到十分痛心
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.16,0:06:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那之前没有任何的药物可以治疗这个疾病
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.88,0:06:34.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是尽管她生病且生命垂危，他仍就与她结婚了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.92,0:06:38.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他想要好好照顾她
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:40.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这对我母亲来说很苦恼
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.32,0:06:43.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为她担心他可能也会感染肺结核
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:46.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.24,0:06:50.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我母亲没有选择的余地
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.60,0:06:56.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在肺结核的阴影下夫妇俩相互鼓励着对方
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.76,0:07:00.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是另一个威胁将要瓦解他们在一起的时间
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.04,0:07:16.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就在理查德和艾琳结婚的一个月前
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.08,0:07:19.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,美国被迫卷入了第二次世界大战
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.40,0:07:21.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在珍珠港袭击事件之后
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:27.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼被问到是否想要加入一项绝密的计划
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:31.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地点在美国新墨西哥州 洛斯·阿拉莫斯 的政府实验室
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.92,0:07:35.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,代号为曼哈顿
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.08,0:07:37.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这项计划的目的就是制造原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.20,0:07:40.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们担心德国
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:43.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,率先研制出恐怖的新式武器
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.68,0:07:45.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后用它们赢得战争
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:51.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就我所知，没有任何事情表明
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.48,0:07:53.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们可以做到，他们不能做到
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.88,0:07:56.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，合作显得至关重要
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.68,0:07:59.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,德国是中心，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.28,0:08:03.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理论物理学家的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:07.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们知道原子弹的威力 如果德国率先研制成功
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.48,0:08:10.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们就不得不确保他们不能统治世界
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.64,0:08:17.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得我应该为了保护文明去做，如果你这样想
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.52,0:08:22.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼成为了曼哈顿计划的一员在洛斯·阿拉莫斯
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.52,0:08:25.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里，他加入了世界上部分最优秀的物理学家的行列
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:29.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,联合他们群体的智慧去制造原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.24,0:08:38.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,奥本海默负责系统学和工程学部分
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.92,0:08:41.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他也是个聪明绝顶的人
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.32,0:08:44.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费米，尼尔斯·玻尔
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.24,0:08:48.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你知道，这些大人物都有极其高的水平
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:08:51.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管杰出的物理学家都聚集在此
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发明原子弹的挑战也来得很快
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.40,0:08:57.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是一个艰巨的任务
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.60,0:08:59.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个根本的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.48,0:09:03.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是需要进行的计算工作量急剧增长
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.24,0:09:06.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有电脑，这工作只好人工去做
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.12,0:09:08.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很大程度上拉慢了进程
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.16,0:09:11.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个问题，在费曼到来之前一直有
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.08,0:09:16.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他发明了一个方法让运算并行实施
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.16,0:09:22.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仍然是手工计算，仍然是每个人一次做一个运算
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.00,0:09:24.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但却是并行工作，并且
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.92,0:09:29.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把每一部分的计算再聚到一起
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:33.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样把3个问题9个月解决的计划
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.20,0:09:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成9个问题在3个月之内解决
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.56,0:09:41.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我把挑战写在黑板上，“我们能作到吗？”，对年青人说
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:44.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们都开始行动“是的，我们将用\N双班轮流制工作，我们会加班加点地工作”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.84,0:09:46.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我们在努力！”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.52,0:09:49.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘结果，我们应对这个问题的速度比以前快了10倍’
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.48,0:09:54.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不知怎么的就将一个团队变成了人类电脑
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.72,0:09:57.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以非人的速度进行工作
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:59.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且能随机应变
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.08,0:10:01.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,之后他的科学前辈们
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.88,0:10:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时的科学大家们
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:07.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一次注意到有这样一号人物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.72,0:10:09.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管作为一个关键人物
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.36,0:10:12.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在战时的最高密的政府项目中
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.40,0:10:16.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼的特立独行和恶作剧从没消停
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.04,0:10:20.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我过去常常开他们的锁
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:22.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘并且告诉他们开他们的锁很容易
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.76,0:10:26.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘每次我们全体开会...所有人一起
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.00,0:10:28.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我就会站起来说我们有重要的机密
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:32.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们不能把机密保存在这样的东西里，我们需要更好的锁
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.60,0:10:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开保险箱和做物理计算
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:40.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,洛斯·阿拉莫斯的生活节奏是无情的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.12,0:10:43.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但对费曼来说，却乐在其中
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.04,0:10:47.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在附近的疗养院
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.44,0:10:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的妻子艾琳卧床不起
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:53.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,疾病一点点地侵害着她
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:10:57.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在当时
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.08,0:11:00.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,干燥的气候被人相信有助于肺结核的好转
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:04.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他在高海拔
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.20,0:11:07.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而她所在的医院在低海拔
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:11.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我记得她去世的那天
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.16,0:11:15.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她才25
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:19.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他才27
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.04,0:11:22.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他非常地伤心
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:31.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而，还没有从悲伤中走出来
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:34.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼就不得不面对他参与
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:36.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,制造原子弹的现实
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:43.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们分发了墨镜以便你可以观看它
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.56,0:11:45.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,20英里之外
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.00,0:11:47.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,透过墨镜你将看不见那个该死的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.84,0:11:50.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不过，我能肯定那东西会伤害你的眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.92,0:11:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,强光决然不会伤害你的眼睛，而是紫外线辐射伤害了你眼睛
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.20,0:11:56.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我躲在一辆卡车的挡风玻璃后面
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:00.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样紫外线辐射不能穿透玻璃，我也就能幸免于难了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.04,0:12:02.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且，我可以看到那个该死的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.96,0:12:10.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我可能是世界上第一个
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:14.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在Trinity试爆的时候真正目睹这个该死的东西的人
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.56,0:12:38.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三周后，美国人准备引爆第二颗原子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:40.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这次，不是测试
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.08,0:12:43.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他曾经...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.72,0:12:49.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,期待作为一个科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:51.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,参与这次飞行
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.36,0:12:56.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这颗炸弹很成功
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.68,0:13:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们觉得他们不需要科学家 ，所以他没有去成
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:05.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不然，他可能就在那架飞机上了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.92,0:13:15.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,炸弹在日本的广岛市上空爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:18.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,时间1945年8月6日
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.48,0:13:20.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它致使超过80000人死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.92,0:13:26.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,3天之后，第二颗原子弹被引爆---在长崎
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.64,0:13:31.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这令人感到十分高兴和振奋
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.84,0:13:36.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,政府和人民都沉浸其中
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.96,0:13:45.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它也造成了一个非常巨大的反差
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.16,0:13:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,洛斯·阿拉莫斯正在发生的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.52,0:13:51.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和同时正发生在广岛的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:53.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼被原子弹的知识深深困扰着
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.96,0:13:56.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他参与的工作导致如此多的死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.56,0:14:03.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在洛斯·阿拉莫斯，他取得了技术层面上的巨大成功
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:07.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后，当然，随后就是一个糟糕的失望...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:12.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,...进行这场巨大的竞赛，然而，竞赛的最后，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.96,0:14:14.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结果并不是很好，事实上...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.76,0:14:18.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,...没什么价值
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.48,0:14:21.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这双重创伤的一个月后-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.32,0:14:23.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,先是，失去了他的妻子
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.24,0:14:26.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随后，他目睹了自己创造的原子弹的破坏力，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:29.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼深陷于痛苦之中
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.28,0:14:33.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许只是因为炸弹本身
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:35.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又可能是因为其他一些心理原因
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.84,0:14:38.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我刚刚失去我的妻子
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.40,0:14:41.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我真的是处在一种十分压抑的状态
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:14:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1945年的秋天
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:01.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼应邀成为教授
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.64,0:15:04.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在康奈尔大学物理系
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:08.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他依旧没有从夏天的那件事中恢复过来
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.20,0:15:11.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们预期我能很好的胜任，于是给了我这样一个工作
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:12.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我并不能胜任
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:15.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我心想“我并没有作出什么重要成果”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.88,0:15:18.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“并且我也从来没有做出什么重要的成果”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:22.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我过去常常沉浸在物理和数学中
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.48,0:15:25.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为我过去常常把玩它们，并不觉得很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.68,0:15:28.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我过去为了取乐经常与它们打交道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.04,0:15:30.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我觉得，我与它们打交道只是为了从中获取乐取
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:35.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当费曼正在物理学中发现乐趣的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.64,0:15:38.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学正处在决定性的时刻
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:42.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,多年来，关于原子行为的新发现
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:44.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使物理学一度陷入混乱
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:48.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于世界的旧的假设已经被证明是错的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.60,0:15:55.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个充满疑问的物理学的新领域叫做量子力学
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.36,0:15:59.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,量子力学，从许多方面来说
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:01.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都给物理学家有史以来
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.76,0:16:04.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从未经历过的最深刻的心理冲击
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.68,0:16:06.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,牛顿是错的
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.40,0:16:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于这个世界，你可以知道你想知道的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而，你还是不能用完美的精度
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.52,0:16:14.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来预测接下来要发生的事
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.76,0:16:17.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,量子力学提出了这样的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:20.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那就是如何准确预测原子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.36,0:16:23.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和它们的电磁力的行为
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.56,0:16:27.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它们是物质世界的基本构成模块
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.84,0:16:31.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它也把其他所有的事情都置于怀疑之中
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.64,0:16:35.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你周围发生的每一件事，除了引力之外
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.88,0:16:39.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有能够直接体验的部分
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:42.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是电磁学在起作用
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.60,0:16:45.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当两个原子聚到一起形成分子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:49.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是电磁学，所以所有的化学都是电磁学
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.60,0:16:52.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而如果这意味着所有的化学都是电磁学
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.36,0:16:54.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那么，你猜怎么着？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.16,0:16:56.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有的生物学都是电磁学
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:01.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自然的，我们周围的每一件事都是电磁学的一种显现
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.68,0:17:03.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以这样或那样的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:09.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个新领域，被称作是量子电动力学，或简称QED，诞生了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.72,0:17:12.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,去试着解释电磁学
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.44,0:17:14.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和亚原子物质
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.48,0:17:17.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些时候QED看上去很有用
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:20.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但有些时候，它的预测错的很离谱
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.08,0:17:25.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这完全是疯了，它没有任何意义，它给我们的结果是无穷
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.48,0:17:27.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无穷并不是一个答案，没有什么东西是无穷的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.84,0:17:30.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们不会在实验室测量无穷大，你得到的是一个有限的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.68,0:17:33.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你不可能由你的基本的物理理论
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.36,0:17:35.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,导出无穷
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.40,0:17:37.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个无穷的预测结果
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.40,0:17:40.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,难住了地球上最聪明的物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.96,0:17:45.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使是QED的发明人，保罗·狄拉克，也困惑不解
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:48.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我还是个孩子的时候，我读过狄拉克的书
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:51.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的这些问题并且没有人知道如何解决
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:52.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正如他书中所述
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.28,0:17:54.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我并不能很好地理解这本书
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.28,0:17:56.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为我还没有达到那个水平
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:17:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在这，在这本书的最后一段，他写道
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:02.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“这里需要一些新的想法”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.40,0:18:05.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此，我在这，这里需要一些新想法
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:08.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好，于是我就开始思考一些新想法
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.04,0:18:09.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能通常看来
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.92,0:18:13.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼新思想的灵感来源非同寻常
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.00,0:18:17.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我在吃午饭的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:20.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一些孩子在自助餐厅扔盘子
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.48,0:18:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,盘子上有蓝色的圆形图案
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:26.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是康奈尔大学自助餐厅的标志
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.68,0:18:29.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当他把盘子扔出去然后盘子落下来时
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.40,0:18:33.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,摇摇晃晃，那个蓝色的图案就像这样在动
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.64,0:18:36.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就想知道这两者有什么联系
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.28,0:18:37.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你瞧，我只是在娱乐
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.52,0:18:39.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一点也不慎重
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.44,0:18:41.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我开始摆弄
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.60,0:18:44.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,旋转事物运动的方程
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.48,0:18:47.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我一直不断地摆弄它
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.28,0:18:50.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随后这个旋转使我想到了一个类似的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.16,0:18:52.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即满足狄拉克方程的
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,电子自旋旋转的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.20,0:18:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就使我重新审视起了
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.80,0:18:57.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,量子电动力学
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.64,0:18:59.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有的东西一倾而出
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.00,0:19:00.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就好像把软木塞从瓶子上
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.52,0:19:01.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,拔掉一样
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.40,0:19:07.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,受到转碟的启发
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.36,0:19:11.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼意识到这个方程导出无穷这一事实
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.24,0:19:13.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并不意味着它们错了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.72,0:19:17.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个问题只是需要从一个新的观点出发来看它
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:20.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实证明,这种挑战非常合适
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.48,0:19:22.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,像费曼这种人
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.52,0:19:26.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可能让你吃惊的是，这种人不喜欢推测
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.68,0:19:29.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不像那种我们所赞美的现代物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:32.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,总是提出新的关于多元宇宙的理论
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:34.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或是自然界的力或者别的什么
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.24,0:19:37.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他很喜欢在这种背景下工作
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.12,0:19:39.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是事情已经很明了了
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.32,0:19:42.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而他比别人知道的更清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:47.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在解决量子电动力学的无穷问题时
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.04,0:19:50.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼提出了一个真正革命性的思想
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:54.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个解法如此奇怪，甚至他的妹妹
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.92,0:19:57.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那时，她也是名物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.16,0:19:59.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也不觉得这是个严肃的工作
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:04.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理查德告诉我说“能帮我到房间里把我的文件拿来吗？”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.16,0:20:07.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我要开始工作，我的文件都在那”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.12,0:20:09.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我走进房间，然后我看见了...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:14.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上面没有数学公式，上面只有些无聊的小图形
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:16.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就走出来对他说
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:17.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“理查德，我找不到你的文件”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.96,0:20:19.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“只有一些像这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.72,0:20:21.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“无聊的图形”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.48,0:20:24.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就说“那就是我的成果！”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.68,0:20:32.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼所发明的这个小图形
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.12,0:20:36.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是一个绝妙的方法，用来回避量子电动力学
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.16,0:20:38.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所需的复杂计算
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:39.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们是一种捷径
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.84,0:20:41.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让他既避免了无穷
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:45.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又可以做出对世界有意义的预测
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.28,0:20:48.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他看出实际上存在一种形象化的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.96,0:20:52.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来思考这些图画，这些方程
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.36,0:20:54.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以把方程中的每一项
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.60,0:20:57.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都与一小幅卡通相联系
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.72,0:21:00.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,今天的人们就把它叫做费曼图
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果换作其他人可能要忙上好几个月
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.52,0:21:05.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而他得到这种方法只用了一个下午
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:07.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,渐渐的，他的图示法使他的思想引起了注意
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.72,0:21:09.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他得到了正确答案
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.68,0:21:11.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而他得到答案的过程更加简单
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管没有一个人明白他在做什么
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:18.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实证明这个方法很有效，现在我们把它应用于
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:21.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,完全不同的领域，一点也不涉及粒子物理学
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.44,0:21:23.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我们看着星系的演变
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.64,0:21:25.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和宇宙中大规模的结构
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:27.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们发现用费曼图
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.56,0:21:31.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来计算这些量也十分有效
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.28,0:21:36.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,量子电动力学
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.80,0:21:39.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一理论，费曼做了一个收尾工作
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.76,0:21:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,该理论也是有史以来数值最精确的物理理论
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.08,0:21:52.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1965年，这一结果被公认
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.16,0:21:54.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼获得了诺贝尔物理学奖
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:57.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他与另外两个物理学家分享了这个奖
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.40,0:22:01.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,朱利安·施温格和朝永振一郎
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.16,0:22:03.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们也在努力解决这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.20,0:22:12.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,解决这个问题值得的诺贝尔奖吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.24,0:22:15.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:19.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,诺贝尔奖的事我完全不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.80,0:22:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不明白这个奖是关于什么的，或者什么东西值得得什么奖
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.84,0:22:25.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果瑞典皇家科学院的人决定
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.48,0:22:28.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谁，谁，谁获得了诺贝尔奖，那就这样吧！
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.72,0:22:31.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为这完全是正确的和适合的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.56,0:22:36.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我会说，这是有史以来颁发的
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:39.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最有价值的诺贝尔奖之一
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.04,0:22:44.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不认为某个瑞典皇家科学院的人决定某项成果得奖
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.24,0:22:47.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这项成果就优秀到值得得奖
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.64,0:22:49.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我已经得到了奖品
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.24,0:22:52.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,奖品就是发现这件事物的喜悦
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.04,0:22:53.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在发现的时候中奖
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.64,0:22:55.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看着别人使用它
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.28,0:22:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那些才是货真价实的！
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.36,0:23:02.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对我来说荣誉是虚的
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.68,0:23:04.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我不相信荣誉
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.84,0:23:06.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它使我感到心烦，荣誉使我感到心烦！
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.64,0:23:09.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,荣誉就是肩章，荣誉就是军服
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.72,0:23:13.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的爸爸带我走上了这条路，\N我受不了荣誉，它深深地伤害了我
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.20,0:23:30.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1959年，在前往欧洲的旅途中
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.04,0:23:33.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼遇见了来自约克郡的女士格温妮丝.豪沃思
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.08,0:23:35.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一年后，他们便结了婚
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.68,0:23:39.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,回到加州，成为加州理工学院的物理学教授的费曼
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.60,0:23:42.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和格温妮丝开始了家庭生活
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:45.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我还是个小孩的时候，我很喜欢父亲给我讲东西
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:50.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我试着给我的孩子讲关于这个世界的有趣的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.96,0:23:52.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是个很棒的父亲
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.80,0:23:56.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,总是在解释事物或研究某事物
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.48,0:23:59.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们会在吃完晚饭后散步，我的父亲和我
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.92,0:24:02.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一起讨论一些事情...就是这样，你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.64,0:24:04.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那很棒而且很愉快
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.04,0:24:13.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我问他什么他就努力试着解释什么
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.36,0:24:20.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,物理的，数学的，历史的，政治的，科幻小说的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.28,0:24:22.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生命的，宇宙的，一切事情
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.32,0:24:28.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我很幸运，我每周有两三天的时间可以和父亲散步问他问题
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.60,0:24:30.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“我们去散个步吧”没问题！
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.72,0:24:36.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理查德·费曼做你的父亲，你的成长路上一定不会无聊
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.40,0:24:38.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,特别是如果你是他的十几岁的女儿
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.52,0:24:45.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的父母买了辆车，一个可以足够我们全家去露营的面包车
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.56,0:24:48.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们在上面画了些图案
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.44,0:24:51.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那种看上去很...很莫名其妙的图案
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.28,0:24:54.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他们平时一点也不喜欢画图案
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.60,0:24:58.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的父亲可能已经对这种尴尬的情况已经有了免疫
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.08,0:25:00.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我肯定受不了！
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.24,0:25:03.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他们却做了，你知道的，那些图还是画上去了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.72,0:25:06.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是许多人以为那是印度的图案
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.56,0:25:09.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我记得有一次我们刚到麦当劳的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.36,0:25:12.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们到停车场去正从车上走下来时
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.44,0:25:15.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有个人就问我们说“为什么你们的面包车上画满了费曼图？”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.80,0:25:18.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我母亲就说“因为我们就是费曼的家人”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.56,0:25:24.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼作为一个科学传播者的名声
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.56,0:25:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,遍布世界各地
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.44,0:25:28.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1960年代早期
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.56,0:25:32.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就开始出席公开演讲，通过电视转播
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.84,0:25:42.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【掌声】
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.36,0:25:52.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我要讨论我们如何寻找一个新的定律
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.52,0:25:55.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一般来说，我们通过下面的流程来寻找一条新定律
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.32,0:25:57.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,首先，我们靠猜
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.32,0:25:58.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【笑声】
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.92,0:26:01.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,别笑，就是这样的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.44,0:26:04.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后我们就来计算这个猜测的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.20,0:26:06.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果它和实验结果不一致...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.84,0:26:10.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,..它就是错的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.24,0:26:13.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一简单的陈述就是科学的关键
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.48,0:26:16.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它和你的猜想有多漂亮没关系
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.24,0:26:18.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它和你有多聪明也没有关系
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.64,0:26:20.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不管是谁提的猜想，或他的名字有多响亮
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.68,0:26:23.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果被实验证明它不可行，那它就是错的
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.64,0:26:25.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如此而已， 岂有他哉!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.64,0:26:27.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【笑声】
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.60,0:26:31.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加州理工学院聘请他为本科生
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.76,0:26:34.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,改写物理课程. 他的新课程
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.12,0:26:37.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,涵盖了整个物理学的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.16,0:26:40.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被称为“费曼物理学讲义”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.08,0:26:45.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有这些课程有一定数量的令人激动的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.48,0:26:49.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并带有一点特殊的风格，你可以
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.44,0:26:52.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把它叫做纯娱乐式表演
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.36,0:26:54.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我相信你们都熟悉这个笑话
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.64,0:26:57.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上全美平均每个家庭
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.68,0:26:59.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大概都有两个半的小孩
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.88,0:27:03.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不管怎样，这绝不意味着任何家庭里有那半个小孩
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.32,0:27:04.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,孩子们都被打包了！
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.76,0:27:06.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【笑声】
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.36,0:27:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他很生动，也讲笑话
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.32,0:27:14.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他用独到的方式解释事物
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.00,0:27:17.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有时那只是个小问题
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.52,0:27:21.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他很有个人魅力，你会觉得那不是在演讲
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.40,0:27:23.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“嗯,那全都讲得通”
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.52,0:27:27.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是，当然，五分钟之后，你不可能真的记住了全部的联系
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.72,0:27:30.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你只是被费曼的个人魅力
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.96,0:27:33.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的幽默，他类比的事例所吸引
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.72,0:27:36.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,研究生开始把他当成偶像来崇拜
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.64,0:27:42.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但到了1960年,他在加州理工学院的课程已经非常出名了
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.88,0:27:48.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在科学之外，费曼的兴趣也十分丰富
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.52,0:27:51.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不光成为了娴熟的邦哥鼓演奏者
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.08,0:27:53.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也发展了自己对油画和素描的热爱
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.76,0:27:55.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是由于他和左赐恩
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.96,0:27:59.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一著名的加州艺术家是好朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.84,0:28:05.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“赐恩”，他说，“你对物理一窍不通”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.68,0:28:08.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“而我对艺术一窍不通”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.28,0:28:11.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“但我们都很欣赏列奥纳多·达·芬奇”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.56,0:28:16.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“你说啥，我们会成为两个达·芬奇？”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.04,0:28:20.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说“这个星期天我给你讲物理”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.40,0:28:23.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“下个星期天，你给我讲艺术”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:28.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当他刚开始的时候，他完全是个业余爱好者
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.04,0:28:31.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是非常，非常...生硬
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.32,0:28:35.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他画了一个我的头像，当时我还
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.96,0:28:38.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时我还很小很好动
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.40,0:28:42.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且，而且那画，你知道他只画了我的，我的头
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.88,0:28:48.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一些头发，还有，还画了一张手像这样摆着
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.12,0:28:53.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以很明显我当时的样子好像在说“哦,我真的不想这样做”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.12,0:28:58.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,画面很单纯，嗯，就是他能看到的姿势
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.12,0:29:03.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我想他可能通过动手
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.60,0:29:10.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,特别是动笔并捕捉人们的特点，获得了绘画的乐趣
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.68,0:29:14.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后，他成为了一位非常娴熟的绘图者
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.20,0:29:22.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼作为一个狂热的学习绘画的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.20,0:29:27.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他甚至花时间到吉安诺尼，帕萨迪纳市的一个脱衣舞吧
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.44,0:29:31.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里，他把注意力集中到画女孩的草图
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.00,0:29:33.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和解物理方程上
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.68,0:29:38.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,别的物理学家对此很费解
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.32,0:29:43.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且说“你知道，费曼本应是个物理学家的”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.20,0:29:47.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“并且是一个非常杰出的物理学家”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.04,0:29:52.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们需要他经常投入在加州理工学院
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.76,0:29:57.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我们需要他来给我们讲授物理”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.00,0:29:59.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是他究竟在干什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.24,0:30:05.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他放下了这些，把他所有的时间都花在歌舞表演女孩
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.52,0:30:08.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,邦哥鼓和艺术上
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.80,0:30:11.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他浪费了太多时间
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.56,0:30:15.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在那些'我不知道他们带给了费曼什么'的人身上
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.28,0:30:20.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我觉得由于费曼结识了许多这样的人
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.64,0:30:24.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,才使他的生活变得多姿多彩
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.32,0:30:29.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1960年，费曼得到了一次年假
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.88,0:30:32.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但不是去别的州的
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.68,0:30:36.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不同的物理系，他只是简单地在加州理工学院校园
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.20,0:30:40.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转向研究另一个一直吸引着他的领域---病毒
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.48,0:30:44.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这期间，他也痴迷于
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.04,0:30:46.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,蚂蚁的社会结构
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.76,0:30:50.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,被纳米技术的潜在应用深深吸引
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.48,0:30:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从长远来看，他对自己今年想要做什么明年想要做什么
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.96,0:31:01.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会考虑一些...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.52,0:31:04.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,弄清一些宇宙的奥秘
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.00,0:31:07.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在日常的工作中
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.08,0:31:11.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他总是寻求，看起来有趣的，好玩的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.28,0:31:16.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直觉上觉得正确的事情去做
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.04,0:31:21.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1980年代早期，他的儿子卡尔所在的
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.52,0:31:25.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,新兴的超级计算机领域这行不可抗拒地吸引了费曼
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.76,0:31:31.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他在波士顿的卡尔的新兴企业报名参加了一个暑期工作
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.04,0:31:34.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们这一伙开创这个公司的都是麻省理工学院的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.68,0:31:37.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是，我们开始运营公司的第一天
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.32,0:31:40.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时，我听到了这样的敲门声，于是我打开门
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.72,0:31:45.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就突然出现在我眼前并向我说\N“费曼前来报到,我的任务是什么？”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.40,0:31:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,紧接着一个敬礼
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.52,0:31:52.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就想“啊哦，我还没想好派给这家伙啥任务！”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.00,0:31:55.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的意思是说，我有了一位获得\N诺贝尔奖的伟大的物理学家...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.84,0:31:58.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，我就开了个简短的会议
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.68,0:32:02.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,试着提出一些适合费曼来做的项目
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.56,0:32:05.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是，有人就说“我们希望你考虑下我们的并行计算
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.88,0:32:08.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的应用程序”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.04,0:32:12.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并行应用处理器用来计算量子色动力学
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.44,0:32:16.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说“不，别胡闹，那，那没什么意义，你知道的”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.72,0:32:18.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“你到底想让我做什么？”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.96,0:32:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就说“好吧，实际上，你知道...”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.04,0:32:24.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我们没有半张纸和笔...”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.44,0:32:26.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就说“好的，我马上就去外面买点回来！”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.92,0:32:31.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这样，他的第一份工作就是出去给公司买文具用品
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.12,0:32:34.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有的回形针和铅笔等等
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.32,0:32:36.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是他的第一个任务
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.92,0:32:41.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这家公司名为“思维机器”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.56,0:32:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,后来成为世界上
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.76,0:32:46.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并行超级计算机行业的重要参与者
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.64,0:32:50.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼用来缩短计算时间的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.08,0:32:55.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是1940年代提出来的, 公司把它带入新的数字时代
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.32,0:32:57.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和一样以往 ，和费曼一起工作
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.96,0:33:00.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,总是充满着乐趣
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.80,0:33:04.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们都很喜欢意大利面条，因为它很容易煮
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.88,0:33:10.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有一次我问他，为什么你把意大利面条弄断的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.32,0:33:13.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它总是断成三节而不是两节呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.20,0:33:15.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你应该试试，真的是这样
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.32,0:33:22.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，当然的，他马上就提出了一个这样的理论
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.96,0:33:25.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他并不满足于这个理论
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.64,0:33:29.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他还设计了一个实验来看看这个理论是否正确
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.04,0:33:32.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实验内容包括将意大利面条慢慢移向桌子边缘
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.60,0:33:34.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后以不同的长度让它折断
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.64,0:33:38.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结果，这个理论被否定，他就提出了另一个理论
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:42.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后每个理论都会导出一个新的实验
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.36,0:33:45.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到了大晚上，我们已经把弄断的意大利面条
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.32,0:33:47.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,搞的到处都是，但我们依然不知道
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.52,0:33:50.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么意大利面条会断成三段
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.24,0:33:58.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种顽皮的好奇心加上被他父亲灌输的
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.76,0:34:03.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,反独裁的价值观，让费曼看上去总是很淘气
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.80,0:34:09.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就是这么的滑稽和玩世不恭
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.04,0:34:14.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你得看看那张照片几分钟然后想着...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.96,0:34:19.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“哦我的天哪,他是真的,你知道！”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.00,0:34:21.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“他在别人头上用手比了一个小角”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.72,0:34:27.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很重要的人士，你知道“嗯，是的，我觉得现在很值得留恋”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.00,0:34:33.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不需要外在的证明
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.04,0:34:35.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他一直受每一个人的尊敬
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.52,0:34:39.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他尊重自己，他知道自己是个特殊的人
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.12,0:34:41.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果他在一些他不认识的家伙面前
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.56,0:34:44.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,表现得像一个笨蛋，这种感觉不错
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.92,0:34:49.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他心里知道自己是个人物
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.16,0:34:56.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1984年，费曼与他的朋友拉夫·莱顿合作
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.80,0:34:59.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用一本幽默书来记录他一生的趣闻轶事
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.16,0:35:06.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我打开了包含所有原子弹的秘密的保险柜’
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.20,0:35:11.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这本书的流行完全是个意外
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.92,0:35:16.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,出版商在1985年1月
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.52,0:35:20.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发布了第一期《别闹了,费曼先生》
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.28,0:35:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一版只印了大概2000册或者更少
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.44,0:35:28.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且在一月份
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.56,0:35:35.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就想，一月份，整个假期都已经结束了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.36,0:35:38.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谁还会在一月份买书啊？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.88,0:35:42.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但人们还真就买了
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.72,0:35:47.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是《别闹了,费曼先生》立刻就变成了畅销书
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.20,0:35:49.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,时至今日
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.08,0:35:53.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它一直都是最畅销科普书之一
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.32,0:35:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我清楚的记得一天晚上我下楼来正看他
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.36,0:36:01.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在，你知道，咯咯地笑
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.60,0:36:05.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显然,他很享受这本他正在读的本书
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.24,0:36:08.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就有点想看看，你知道，“你在读什么？”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.84,0:36:12.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是他举起书，我就看到了，那是写他自己的书
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.60,0:36:16.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《别闹了,费曼先生》，他就说“啊，很有个性啊”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.64,0:36:23.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直率地承认了自己，是的，他在嘲笑着自己的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.56,0:36:27.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这本书生动地描绘了费曼的世界观
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.60,0:36:31.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好奇感和好玩感引导着他的一生
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.36,0:36:35.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世界各地更多的观众通过一系列的BBC纪录片，广播
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.84,0:36:39.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来更好的走进费曼
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.08,0:36:49.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我有位艺术家朋友，他有时采取这样一种观点
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.16,0:36:51.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个我并不赞同的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.76,0:36:56.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你拿起一朵花然后说“看它多漂亮”这我同意
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.60,0:36:59.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他说，我是个艺术家，可以看懂这花的美丽
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.72,0:37:01.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是你，作为一个科学家
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.32,0:37:04.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把它研究透了，它也就变得索然无味了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.48,0:37:06.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为他的想法有点怪
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.96,0:37:10.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,首先，他看到的美对其他人而言都是等价的
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.88,0:37:12.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对我也一样
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.48,0:37:16.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我相信，尽管我没有像他那样
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.00,0:37:20.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有十分雅致的审美，但我依然可以赞美那朵花的美丽
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.12,0:37:23.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同时，关于这朵花，我看到的比他更多
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.84,0:37:27.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我可以想象它的细胞，它里面的复杂反应
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.32,0:37:28.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那同样很美
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.96,0:37:32.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的意思是说，它的美丽不光表现在这种程度上
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.64,0:37:36.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在更微观的世界里它也同样美丽，它的内部结构
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.28,0:37:38.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的反应过程也是
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.24,0:37:43.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上花的颜色和它的逐渐进化是为了
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.48,0:37:47.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使昆虫更青睐于给它授粉
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.20,0:37:50.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就意味着昆虫可以看见花的颜色
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.24,0:37:51.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也萌生了一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.68,0:37:55.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种美感也存在于低等生物里吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.16,0:37:57.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它为什么会审美？
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.36,0:38:03.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一朵带有香气的和神秘感的令人着迷的花
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.16,0:38:07.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,科学知识只是将各种有趣的问题附加给它
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.40,0:38:10.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它只是附加，我不知道如何减去
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.64,0:38:13.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大多数人只有几个故事
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.32,0:38:16.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你或者我，可能有那么三两个故事可说
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.48,0:38:20.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有的人可能有十个，而费曼有数百个
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.56,0:38:24.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且费曼极具魅力
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.64,0:38:27.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为克里斯.赛克斯在他的纪录片中
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.64,0:38:30.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很好的抓住了费曼的形象
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.00,0:38:33.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,片中的一切都表现出费曼在发现事物
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.16,0:38:35.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和探索生命时所获得的巨大的快乐
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.80,0:38:38.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不仅如此，他在告诉你的时候更是显示出极大的快感
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.84,0:38:41.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为他对解决问题感到很满足
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.04,0:38:44.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且他能与许多人交流
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.68,0:38:47.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,分享自己对世界对大自然的看法等等
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.40,0:38:53.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我还是加州理工学院的学生时，我走到费曼的门口
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.24,0:38:56.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后敲门，门开了，我解释说
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.88,0:38:59.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我妈妈看了他的有关他自己的节目
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.44,0:39:02.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,认为他很有趣，她没有科学背景
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.60,0:39:04.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说，“你看你能不能给她写封信
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.88,0:39:08.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“因为这样我可能就有机会教她物理学？”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.08,0:39:11.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后费曼就真给她写了封信. 在信中他说
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.36,0:39:16.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“亲爱的乔恩女士.  不要理睬你儿子想教你物理的尝试.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.08,0:39:20.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“物理不是最重要的事情. 爱才是最重要的”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.88,0:39:22.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这样，真是事与愿违啊.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.80,0:39:25.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我遇到了那时候最伟大的活着的物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.32,0:39:27.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他却告诉我妈妈说物理学不重要
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.96,0:39:29.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,爱才是重要的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.96,0:39:45.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过他的电影和书籍，费曼影响了许多人的生活
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.04,0:39:48.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但有些事情不会因为
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.56,0:39:50.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,成功和认知而改变
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:56.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我经常跑步，然后费曼就想
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.24,0:40:00.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,嘿，这事有益身心健康啊，于是他也开始跑步
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.52,0:40:05.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且当跑步成为你的生活的一部分时，你就可以减肥了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.16,0:40:09.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后费曼忽然感觉腹部的一侧有什么东西凸出来了
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.28,0:40:14.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们就发现在他的腹腔下有一个大肿块
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.68,0:40:16.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他回到家告诉我们说
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.04,0:40:18.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“它有橄榄球那么大，几乎耗损了一整个肾脏”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.76,0:40:21.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他接着说“没事，我去过医学图书馆”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.00,0:40:22.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我知道这东西而且我断定”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.92,0:40:25.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“这东西只有30%的可能要了我的命”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.64,0:40:30.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以，你知道，你不会想从你父亲那听到这样的事
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.12,0:40:34.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他却告诉了我们这一事实
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.00,0:40:36.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.16,0:40:39.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他辞掉了当时的工作，因为，你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.88,0:40:43.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,手术和化疗等等，得没日没夜的做
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.56,0:40:47.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有一天他的秘书海伦·塔克给我打电话
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.84,0:40:50.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,告诉我迪克得了癌症，下个星期五
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.88,0:40:52.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要去医院做手术
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.72,0:40:55.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那是个非常危险的手术
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.16,0:40:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且这个手术不一定能保证他活下来
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.88,0:41:01.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我保证不告诉其他人，而且他\N并不知道我了解到的有关他的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.80,0:41:06.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就告诉他在我们合作发表的计算中
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.08,0:41:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有人发现了其中存在一个明显的错误
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.32,0:41:12.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是，在星期一的早上，我们在我的办公室碰头
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.32,0:41:17.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他就坐下来开始解题，随即便沉浸于此
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.44,0:41:21.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他所有的精力和注意力都放在求解这个问题上了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.32,0:41:23.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就这样，我们一起忙了一整天
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.44,0:41:25.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最后在晚上七点钟的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.80,0:41:28.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们觉得这个问题很棘手，解不出来
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.96,0:41:31.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们没办法算出答案是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.28,0:41:33.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我们就都放弃回家去了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.32,0:41:37.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,两个小时后，他在家就打电话给我，\N告诉我说他解决了那个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.32,0:41:40.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不可能放弃，也不可能罢手
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.80,0:41:42.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,最终他找到了解决方案
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.52,0:41:45.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他把答案通过电话口述给我，\N告诉我答案是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.72,0:41:48.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且十分兴奋，完全都飘飘然了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.56,0:41:53.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼从第一次癌症手术中恢复了过来
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.00,0:41:56.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这一疾病再也不会从他身上完全消失
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.00,0:41:59.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他将一直要活在病魔的阴影下
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.80,0:42:14.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我们的主引擎已经启动，四，三，二，一，发射了”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.12,0:42:17.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第二十五次航天飞行任务起航
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.36,0:42:20.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它照亮了发射塔
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.44,0:42:23.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,挑战者号开始转身指令
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.00,0:42:25.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘罗杰，转动，挑战者号
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.04,0:42:27.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘转的不错
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.64,0:42:33.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1986年1月，美国宇航局(NASA)启动第25次航天飞行任务
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.68,0:42:37.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它象征着一个太空飞行的新纪元，因为一个中学老师
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.96,0:42:40.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,克丽斯塔•麦考利夫也加入了队伍
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.88,0:42:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘第65条执行完毕，谢谢’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.60,0:42:47.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我是挑战者.现在节流控制上调
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.00,0:42:54.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我正在上社会课程，我记得我们当时正在考试
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.96,0:42:58.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,老师就走进来说“我们遇到了一个可怕的事故”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.68,0:43:08.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“飞行控制器在这里密切关注形势”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.16,0:43:09.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我们没有下行线路’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.68,0:43:14.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后回到家，我的父母已经看了全过程
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.00,0:43:17.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这太不寻常了，因为平时他们不会\N一本正经地坐在电视机前
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.04,0:43:20.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘仔细看看你的资料’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.04,0:43:22.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把你所有的显示复印下来
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.80,0:43:25.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘确保你所保护的任何数据源’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.80,0:43:30.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,电视直播了他们失去的航天飞机和7名宇航员
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.12,0:43:34.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,此事震惊了美国，全国陷入哀痛之中
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.08,0:43:39.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,国家的损失首先是我们宇航员个人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.84,0:43:42.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的家庭，朋友，爱人
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.80,0:43:45.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的彻底损失
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.36,0:43:49.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但有一个问题所有人都想知道答案--
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.32,0:43:51.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,到底是什么出了问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.64,0:43:56.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,总统委员会马上被召集起来以查明原因
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.68,0:44:00.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个委员会是由大量的与NASA
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.16,0:44:02.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关系密切的业内人士担任的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.76,0:44:08.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,委员会还需要有声望的利益不相关的科学界人士
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.72,0:44:12.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我有一个行事原则，从来不接近首都华盛顿
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.76,0:44:15.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我打电话给我的各种朋友
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.20,0:44:18.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们或多或少都与这项太空计划有关
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.48,0:44:20.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就试着去问他们是否考虑过
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.92,0:44:24.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我是不是也应该参与调查或者别的人也可以来调查
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.28,0:44:26.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的朋友就说“迪克，你应该去”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.36,0:44:29.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“因为你是唯一可以揭穿谎言的人”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.84,0:44:32.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他问我，我认为他该做什么
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.04,0:44:35.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就问他“你觉得这是个很重要的问题吗？”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.28,0:44:36.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说,是的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.72,0:44:38.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“你觉得你责无旁贷吗？”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.88,0:44:41.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,过了一会，他说“嗯,是啊,也许可以”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.84,0:44:43.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就再没说什么了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.32,0:44:46.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,犹豫了几分钟之后，他说“见鬼去吧，希布斯”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.60,0:44:47.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后就挂了
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.76,0:44:54.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼打破了自己的原则，事故之后的几天
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.72,0:44:57.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他也加入了在华盛顿的调查
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.96,0:45:02.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,调查的负责人是威廉·罗杰斯
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.92,0:45:06.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,前国务卿和华盛顿消息灵通人士
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.92,0:45:10.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他那一套正式的，官僚主义的方式
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.68,0:45:14.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,与随心所欲，特立独行的教授截然相反
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.72,0:45:18.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但罗杰斯先生并不知道这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.64,0:45:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,之前我登上过失事飞船，于是我抓住机会
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.84,0:45:25.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“嘿,我刚好做过一项调查,”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.40,0:45:27.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“你想看看吗?”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.44,0:45:29.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我觉得当时罗杰斯很不情愿地说
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.04,0:45:30.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“嗯，行，你可以拿给我们看看”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.64,0:45:32.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“但是我们不会这样做”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.76,0:45:35.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此我就审查了这份非常逻辑化的规范流程
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.80,0:45:39.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这份流程适用于调查太空事故，而罗杰斯说
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.48,0:45:42.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“不，我们没有这个技术能力按这种方式做”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.12,0:45:44.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个时候费曼插了一杠子
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.08,0:45:46.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说“不，我觉得很好，我觉得那是个聪明的方法”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.20,0:45:50.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对费曼和主席来说
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.28,0:45:53.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是他们不好关系的开始
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.28,0:45:56.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是对教授和空军上将 来说
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.16,0:45:59.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是他们好关系的开始
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.20,0:46:01.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是这个世界上最聪明的人
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.84,0:46:06.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且他也有着为人正直的好名声，你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.28,0:46:09.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他是这个世界上最诚实的人
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.68,0:46:15.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他从不接受任何事情，除非他真的可以证明它
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.88,0:46:21.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这两人开始游历全美
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.16,0:46:24.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,拜访了制造太空飞船的NASA的协助单位
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.08,0:46:27.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,询问了工程师和管理者们
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.44,0:46:31.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在和工程师们对话的过程中，他注意到
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.48,0:46:34.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“哦,他们中的一些人现在不愿和我说话”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.36,0:46:37.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“因为那些管理者在房间里”你知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.00,0:46:40.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这并不是一个简单的技术问题
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.08,0:46:44.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里面也掺杂了人为迷局
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.00,0:46:46.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在写给家里的米歇尔和格文内斯的信中
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.72,0:46:50.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼对他猎取到的真相
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.56,0:46:52.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,表达了他的失望和兴奋
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.80,0:46:56.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘亲爱的米歇尔和格文内斯’
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.04,0:46:59.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘这是我第一次有时间给你们写信’
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.28,0:47:03.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我已经确实已经像猫一样闻到了\N老鼠的味道，绝对不会忘记，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.20,0:47:07.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘我很爱这个味道，那是令人激动的冒险的开始’
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.44,0:47:14.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但当下有一个问题，NASA的经理不愿透露
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.76,0:47:17.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们全部的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.84,0:47:22.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那个结论是个障眼法
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.76,0:47:28.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,NASA想要控制对委员会提供的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.36,0:47:32.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并隐瞒真实的情况
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.36,0:47:33.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们不是撒谎
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.80,0:47:37.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他们也不会真的到处去泄露真相
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.68,0:47:41.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼所不知道的是
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.24,0:47:44.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,库缇娜上将在美国宇航局有一个秘密的消息源
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.80,0:47:48.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,萨莉·莱德是登陆太空的第一位女性
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.68,0:47:51.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也是另一个委员会成员
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.48,0:47:55.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,她私下里告诉上将NASA一直怀疑
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.40,0:47:57.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用于航天飞机固体火箭助推器的
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.04,0:48:00.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,O型塑胶垫圈
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.08,0:48:02.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在寒冷气候下的工作状况
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.00,0:48:06.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发射的那天早晨，发射站的温度达到了冰点以下
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.12,0:48:09.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上将需要把这一信息告诉费曼
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.40,0:48:11.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,又不损害他的消息来源
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.00,0:48:18.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,机会终于在一天晚饭后的库缇娜的房子里等到了
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.32,0:48:21.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上将修理他的老爷车
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.08,0:48:24.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我把他带到车库向他展示那辆老爷车
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.04,0:48:26.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但费曼真的对车不怎么感兴趣
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.88,0:48:30.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我们就绕过车子，接着我就向他展示了内部结构
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.92,0:48:33.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我告诉他哪是引擎
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.36,0:48:35.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这时费曼看到了我的工作台
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.44,0:48:38.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他看到一对汽化器摆在那
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.16,0:48:40.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他就说“库缇娜，那些是汽化器吗？”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.92,0:48:44.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“哦，它们产自澳宝，我把放在了一起的”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.96,0:48:47.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“其中一个拿起来拆开清理了一下”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.40,0:48:49.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这时一个想法出现在我脑海中
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.72,0:48:54.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我要把寒冷、O型环和泄漏的想法提出来
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.88,0:48:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“你知道吗，教授，这些该死的汽化器的O型环”
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.36,0:49:01.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“总是因为寒冷的原因而泄漏”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.44,0:49:07.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼有了答案，同时他也有了一个启发性的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:11.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来把这个答案告知公众媒体
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.00,0:49:19.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从那件事情和各种事情，你告诉我
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.36,0:49:22.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于弹性的需求和弹性的缺乏
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.60,0:49:25.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当和委员会第二次会晤时，他开始质问
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.36,0:49:28.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,高级工程师关于发射那天早上
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.84,0:49:31.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,寒冷气候对O型环的影响
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.32,0:49:33.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们的回应就是托词
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.44,0:49:36.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,否认温度会对它造成影响
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.84,0:49:43.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在出事之前，从我们所知的信息
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.64,0:49:45.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和我们已经明白的事实
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.88,0:49:48.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,难道还不能重视在某个温度下
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.76,0:49:53.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,任何一处的垫圈会变的不安全吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.40,0:49:58.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有一些关于温度的问题是否
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.28,0:50:01.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在RS...RSB(助推器)上，我想你们这样称呼它...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.12,0:50:04.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是的，是这样叫的...是不适合的？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.00,0:50:07.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一判断只是基于我们所看到的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.40,0:50:10.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发射那天，我们运行的装配
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.68,0:50:13.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种垫圈在这种温度下依然有效
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.16,0:50:14.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是最终的结果
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.92,0:50:17.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是费曼的机会
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.36,0:50:20.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他决定利用经典的科学演示实验的力量
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.04,0:50:25.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在听证会期间，在他们谈到关于O型环接点的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.92,0:50:27.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对方避而不谈
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.92,0:50:29.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,轮到费曼时
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.64,0:50:34.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我坐在他的左手边把东西递给他，他把东西放在桌上
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.84,0:50:39.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,之后他把手伸进自己的荷包掏出一把钳子，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.92,0:50:44.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,软管夹和螺丝刀，把接点拆开
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.16,0:50:48.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,抽出一段O型橡胶环，把它夹在螺丝钳上
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.04,0:50:49.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后我就知道了他准备干嘛了
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.84,0:50:54.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他看着冰水，并发誓说那是偶尔想到的
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.12,0:50:58.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他有了这个想法“等一下，我知道，知道是怎么回事”
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.00,0:51:02.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我可以得到当橡胶变冷时的数据”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.04,0:51:07.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他夹住一段橡胶然后把它放在装着冰水的烧杯里
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.24,0:51:12.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我把这个取自你们密封舱的垫圈放进冰水里
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.84,0:51:16.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,随后我就发现当你对它施加压力保持一会儿
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.68,0:51:20.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,再释放压力，它保持变形状态，没有再反弹回去
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.32,0:51:22.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一直保持着这个尺寸
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.76,0:51:25.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,换句话说，至少几秒钟，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.28,0:51:28.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者比这个时间多几秒，这种特殊的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.48,0:51:33.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在32度时就没有弹性了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.16,0:51:37.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我相信这对我们的问题至关重要
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.88,0:51:46.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那个O型环本应该是密封在
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.36,0:51:50.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,固体助推器的密封舱内，当它变得很冷的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.60,0:51:55.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就失去了弹性和填补助推器之间的空隙的能力了
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.32,0:52:01.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么燃料会泄露和航天飞机会爆炸
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.76,0:52:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼这一举，板上钉钉
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.52,0:52:06.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,证实了在发射的73秒后
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.96,0:52:10.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为寒冷而导致航天飞机的失事
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.56,0:52:14.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这次调查是一个真正的转折点
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.36,0:52:15.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它决然不能被忽视
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.20,0:52:22.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1986年的夏天，该委员会的报告被提交了上去
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.08,0:52:25.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在报告的附录中，费曼加了一个严肃的
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.72,0:52:28.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于科学的局限性的提醒
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.16,0:52:30.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他最后的建议，我认为
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.44,0:52:32.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是真正的一小段总结
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.72,0:52:36.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于一个成功的技术
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.92,0:52:41.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现实必须置于比公共关系优先的地位
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.80,0:52:43.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为大自然是不会被愚弄的
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.40,0:52:54.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我还记得，癌症对他的负担有多大
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.68,0:52:58.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他非常的疲惫，他来拜访我时，他说
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.84,0:53:03.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我来是来告诉你我的癌症又复发了
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.76,0:53:08.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看起来并不乐观
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.12,0:53:11.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但我忘记了我们谈论的内容，并且也忘了
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.28,0:53:13.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我是怎么转到这个话题的
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.80,0:53:18.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“ 我在思考在一个紊流中的不变量”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.80,0:53:20.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他问“你是什么意思？”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.84,0:53:24.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我稍微解释了一下那究竟是怎么回事
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.04,0:53:25.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,那个不变量，你知道的
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.84,0:53:29.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我说“在这些，那些和那样的条件下”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.92,0:53:31.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说“让我们看看”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.96,0:53:34.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就拿出了一个笔记本
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.20,0:53:39.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他拿着笔记本就开始算，他把步骤一步一步地写下来
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.28,0:53:43.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我记得他写到13步的时候得到了结果
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.36,0:53:47.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说“是的，那是真的，它确实是个不变量”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.20,0:53:53.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他说“你让我又重回了一遍物理的思考”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.28,0:53:55.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我现在可以回家了”
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.16,0:54:02.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1988的二月，费曼在医院度过了他的最后时光
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.84,0:54:05.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的肾脏不行了并且他决定
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.88,0:54:09.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不打算通过透析来延长自己的痛苦
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.96,0:54:15.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我仍稍稍想过“不，事情不应该是这样的”
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.84,0:54:19.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但只要他的头脑清醒依然可以解决
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.88,0:54:22.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很多的物理难题
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.28,0:54:27.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当一个人临终前，他们的手会这样动
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.44,0:54:33.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当时在那里的护士说他并不是
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.52,0:54:37.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,试着要交流，那种举动很正常
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.16,0:54:45.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他就把手像这样举起来
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.32,0:54:53.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他就想这样做，这个，如果你知道，那是
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.36,0:54:57.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,魔术师当他们准备变东西的时候所做的动作，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.32,0:54:58.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他就这样做...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.16,0:55:08.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他再一次通过这种方式交流了对世界的看法
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.68,0:55:11.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,医生错了，他听得见
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.72,0:55:14.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果他尽力还是可以动的
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.92,0:55:19.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也可以理解...他可以听到和理解正在说的事
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.60,0:55:21.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是他最后的遗言
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.08,0:55:28.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理查德·费曼于1988年2月15日
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.56,0:55:32.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在洛杉矶的医院去世，年仅69岁
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.08,0:55:39.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我最后一次和理查德·费曼散步时，他告诉了我
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.12,0:55:44.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,许多有趣的故事，但我意识到，这些故事背后的信息就是
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.20,0:55:49.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼将死于癌症，这让我很伤心
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.32,0:55:55.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而他察觉到了这点，就问我“怎么了？”
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.28,0:55:59.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就说“我伤心是因为我觉得你将不久于人世”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.24,0:56:05.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他说“是啊，这个问题有时我也头疼”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.88,0:56:12.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“但并不是你想的那样”他说“因为你意识到了”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.04,0:56:17.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“在你生命中的某个时刻，你讲了很多故事”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.48,0:56:21.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“并且这些故事在你离去之后仍会继续流传”
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.16,0:56:26.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,今天，他离开我们已经有25年多了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.48,0:56:30.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,费曼的预言已经成为现实，而且现实已经超过了他的设想
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.92,0:56:34.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过一项发明，费曼的故事依然流传
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.36,0:56:36.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这项发明在费曼去世时还没有呢
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.80,0:56:41.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为通过在互联网上的重加工
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.40,0:56:45.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,新一代的人们发现了费曼的快乐时光
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.88,0:56:54.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你只要在谷歌中输入费曼，或理查德·费曼
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.16,0:56:59.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,任何类似的词语，就能找到有关的东西，真是太奇妙了
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.36,0:57:04.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你在那里可以找到许多费曼的材料
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.20,0:57:08.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我看到我父亲在许多现在的大众文化中被引用，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.88,0:57:10.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,次数比他活着的时候还多
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.24,0:57:18.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我有位艺术家朋友，他有时采取这样一种观点
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.96,0:57:21.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个我并不赞同的观点
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.44,0:57:25.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你拿起一朵花然后说“看它多漂亮”这我同意
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.64,0:57:28.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他说，我是个艺术家，可以看懂这花的美丽
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.56,0:57:33.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是你，作为一个科学家，\N把它研究透了，它也就变得索然无味了
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.04,0:57:35.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为他的想法有点怪
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.36,0:57:40.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你一定想知道互联网上的费曼会是个什么样子
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.88,0:57:43.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为他真的,真的会很喜欢这个主意
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.88,0:57:50.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,通过或长或短的剪辑将他传播到世界各地
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.28,0:57:54.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,的因特网上，也许每时每刻都在传，我认为他会喜欢的
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.20,0:57:56.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你知道的，你只要像这样触碰一下它...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.64,0:57:57.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【费曼的声音】
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.96,0:58:00.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,...你马上就把他的声音带了回来，你知道的
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.88,0:58:03.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“整个宇宙都在一杯酒中”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.92,0:58:07.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“我不觉得我们会知道在何种意义上他要这样比喻”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.80,0:58:09.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,【笑声】
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.40,0:58:12.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,‘因为诗人不喜欢被理解’
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.88,0:58:16.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我知道我会记得他
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.96,0:58:21.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,作为一个好兄弟和一个好人
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.88,0:58:27.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他不光是一个科学家，也不光是一个艺术家
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.76,0:58:29.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也不光是一个教育家
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.52,0:58:32.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他本人就是人性化的物理学
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.20,0:58:35.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他证明了要成为一个顶级的物理学家
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.04,0:58:36.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你不用不食人间烟火
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.72,0:58:39.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我认为对于那些想从事科学研究的人来说
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.64,0:58:41.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是费曼留给他们的一项重要遗产
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.20,0:58:43.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这项遗产就是一个人的努力，是他展示给我们
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.12,0:58:52.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,理查德•费曼曾经鼓舞你去走自己的人生之路吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.88,0:58:57.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,加入开放大学探索你的选择和了解更多
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.20,0:59:00.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,关于他如何彻底变革了物理学的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.60,0:59:02.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,请访问：
